1
00:03:53,023 --> 00:03:54,023
Ten hut.

2
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,486
Briggs and Hudson, fall out.

3
00:03:57,528 --> 00:04:01,157
Sergeant Williams, take
charge.

4
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:04,535
The Ardona's comin' in.

5
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:06,662
If we don't get Horn down
to the dock for cigarettes,

6
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:09,415
these boys will tear down
his store.

7
00:04:12,209 --> 00:04:14,128
Let me go, let me go!

8
00:04:17,256 --> 00:04:18,048
I got you.

9
00:04:18,090 --> 00:04:19,008
Lie there.

10
00:04:19,049 --> 00:04:21,385
Fall dead, don't get up.

11
00:04:27,641 --> 00:04:29,685
Hello mother, how's it by you,
today?

12
00:04:29,727 --> 00:04:30,895
How are you this morning?

13
00:04:30,936 --> 00:04:32,563
Kinda chewy this morning,
ain't we?

14
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:37,401
Come on, give me a lift.

15
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:38,652
All together now.

16
00:04:38,694 --> 00:04:39,694
Heave-ho.

17
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:42,573
Now tell us Mama,

18
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:43,532
where's the old man?

19
00:04:43,574 --> 00:04:44,575
What do you want, huh?

20
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:45,659
Cigarettes.

21
00:04:45,701 --> 00:04:46,952
Cigarettes, no got here.

22
00:04:46,994 --> 00:04:47,787
That's just it.

23
00:04:47,828 --> 00:04:48,828
Where's Horn?

24
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:51,999
Asleep, huh?

25
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:52,958
Well, we'll have that bird on
his feet

26
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,919
and down to the docks,
chop-chop, pronto.

27
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,128
I think so, no.

28
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,630
I think so, yes.

29
00:04:57,671 --> 00:04:58,671
Get him, boys.

30
00:04:59,715 --> 00:05:00,800
What's the matter, Mama?

31
00:05:00,841 --> 00:05:02,259
The old man acting up again?

32
00:05:02,301 --> 00:05:03,594
How you talk?

33
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:04,762
What do you say?

34
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:06,222
My husband is a very good man.

35
00:05:06,263 --> 00:05:08,432
What's all this?

36
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:09,725
What's all this?

37
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,227
Relax.

38
00:05:11,268 --> 00:05:12,268
Where am I?

39
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:15,063
Home.

40
00:05:15,856 --> 00:05:16,649
To be sure.

41
00:05:16,690 --> 00:05:17,817
The Arduna's is in, Joe.

42
00:05:17,858 --> 00:05:18,901
Well, what of it?

43
00:05:18,943 --> 00:05:20,694
No candy corn, no sardines,

44
00:05:20,736 --> 00:05:22,488
no bacon, no corned beef.

45
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:23,531
And no cigarettes.

46
00:05:24,865 --> 00:05:26,033
On your feet, mate.

47
00:05:26,075 --> 00:05:27,618
Fall in.

48
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:28,744
Wait, wait.

49
00:05:29,703 --> 00:05:32,373
Much too early in the
morning for life's burdens.

50
00:05:32,414 --> 00:05:33,541
Wipe your chin.

51
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:35,584
Oh well,

52
00:05:35,626 --> 00:05:36,961
if I must, I must.

53
00:05:39,296 --> 00:05:40,172
Have your landing cards

54
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:41,799
and passports ready, please.

55
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:44,677
Have your landing cards and
passports ready, please.

56
00:05:46,387 --> 00:05:47,972
Let me see.

57
00:05:48,013 --> 00:05:50,224
You want my passport, don't you?

58
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:51,308
Yes, ma'am.

59
00:05:53,477 --> 00:05:56,146
My husband and I usually
use the same passport.

60
00:05:56,188 --> 00:05:58,190
We have separate ones this time,

61
00:05:58,232 --> 00:06:00,234
in case I should wish to
visit the other island

62
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:02,361
while he's working.

63
00:06:02,403 --> 00:06:04,321
I wonder why it must rain.

64
00:06:04,363 --> 00:06:05,865
Doesn't it ever stop?

65
00:06:05,906 --> 00:06:07,741
Yes, ma'am.

66
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:10,411
A little more efficiency

67
00:06:10,452 --> 00:06:12,997
and we wouldn't be kept
waiting so long.

68
00:06:13,038 --> 00:06:13,914
Have your landing cards

69
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:15,016
and passports ready, please.

70
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,376
Wait just a minute.

71
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:18,418
There you are.

72
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:25,551
Landing cards and
passports ready, please.

73
00:06:27,803 --> 00:06:29,889
Landing cards and passports
ready, please.

74
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:40,274
Thank you, just put it down
please.

75
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:41,317
By the way, officer.

76
00:06:41,358 --> 00:06:43,861
I was wondering, what
does Pongo Pongo mean?

77
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,779
I don't think it means
anything at all, sir.

78
00:06:45,821 --> 00:06:47,489
Then it's certainly well
named.

79
00:06:50,534 --> 00:06:51,911
Unusual weather, of course.

80
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,580
Of course.

81
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:56,415
What will it be like in Apia?

82
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:57,541
Unusual.

83
00:07:00,961 --> 00:07:01,879
Have your landing cards

84
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:04,256
and passports ready, please.

85
00:07:08,093 --> 00:07:09,845
Welcome to Pongo Pongo,
Mr. Davidson.

86
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:11,698
Thank you, but we'll only
be here for an hour or two.

87
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,641
We're taking a schooner
this afternoon to Apia.

88
00:07:13,682 --> 00:07:14,910
Not this afternoon,
I'm afraid.

89
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:16,768
Sorry, sir.

90
00:07:20,022 --> 00:07:21,023
Thank you.

91
00:07:23,984 --> 00:07:25,819
What's the matter, Alfred?

92
00:07:25,861 --> 00:07:26,946
Has anything happened?

93
00:07:26,987 --> 00:07:27,821
Unwelcome news.

94
00:07:27,863 --> 00:07:29,573
We cannot sail for
Apia this afternoon.

95
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:30,950
Not sail today?

96
00:07:30,991 --> 00:07:32,117
Why?

97
00:07:32,159 --> 00:07:33,553
One of the sailors
aboard the schooner

98
00:07:33,577 --> 00:07:34,703
has come down with cholera.

99
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:36,747
We cannot start
until it is certain

100
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:39,708
that none of the rest of
the crew are effected.

101
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,460
It may mean a delay
of several days.

102
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:43,337
I think I'd prefer the cholera.

103
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,756
But where can we stay?

104
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:47,091
The General Store.

105
00:07:47,132 --> 00:07:48,132
Hip, hip.

106
00:07:49,176 --> 00:07:50,636
There's Mr. Horn, now.

107
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:51,678
Mr. Horn?

108
00:07:53,722 --> 00:07:56,725
Well, upon my soul.

109
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:58,394
This is a treat.

110
00:07:58,435 --> 00:07:59,853
How do you do, Mrs. Davidson?

111
00:07:59,895 --> 00:08:00,896
Greetings, Mr. Horn.

112
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,690
Our poor island is honored.

113
00:08:02,731 --> 00:08:05,109
Dr. and Mrs. MacPhaill,
Mr. Horn.

114
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:06,402
How do you do?

115
00:08:06,443 --> 00:08:07,236
You're leaving soon?

116
00:08:07,277 --> 00:08:08,821
No, the schooner
for Apia is delayed

117
00:08:08,862 --> 00:08:09,780
on account of the cholera.

118
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:11,907
We shall have to ask you
to put us up.

119
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:12,950
That's tough luck,

120
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:15,577
for you folks, I mean.

121
00:08:15,619 --> 00:08:16,662
Can nothing be done?

122
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,504
Clearly possible I can
persuade the governor

123
00:08:18,539 --> 00:08:19,915
to make an exception
in our case,

124
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,333
I'm going to see him now.

125
00:08:28,632 --> 00:08:29,425
Hey, Joe.

126
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:31,802
If my guests will pardon
me for a few minutes,

127
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:34,722
they shall have my personal
escort to the hotel.

128
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:37,850
What's the matter, Joe?

129
00:08:37,891 --> 00:08:39,935
If there's anything
I hate, it's reformers.

130
00:08:39,977 --> 00:08:42,646
Huh? So that's what's
the matter with them?

131
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:45,065
Yeah, you'd better
watch yourself

132
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:47,359
while that lovely couple
is on the island.

133
00:08:47,401 --> 00:08:49,528
They'll break your back
to save your souls.

134
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:50,654
What's his badge?

135
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:53,824
An investigator
of Navy Conditions.

136
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,993
A professional reformer.

137
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:58,370
He wields more influence
in the South Seas

138
00:08:58,412 --> 00:08:59,580
than the sun, the planets,

139
00:08:59,621 --> 00:09:00,998
and the American government.

140
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:04,835
Pearls of wisdom.

141
00:09:06,503 --> 00:09:08,672
Pearls of wisdom.

142
00:09:11,216 --> 00:09:13,093
Now look here,

143
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:15,262
you may take the
British lion by the tail,

144
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:16,346
you may twist it,

145
00:09:16,388 --> 00:09:17,347
you may jerk it,

146
00:09:17,389 --> 00:09:18,557
you may yank it,

147
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:21,101
you may tie it in
a big bow knot,

148
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:22,227
but dash it all,

149
00:09:22,269 --> 00:09:24,146
you can't pull it out
by the roots.

150
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:26,940
I say, can't you take a joke?

151
00:09:29,109 --> 00:09:30,277
Hello lads, boys.

152
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:31,904
I want you to meet Thompson.

153
00:09:31,945 --> 00:09:33,614
Sadie, meet the boys.

154
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:35,783
Boys.

155
00:09:35,824 --> 00:09:37,284
And this is Mr. Horn.

156
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:40,704
Mr. Horn, your climate's
bummed.

157
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:41,538
Sorry, Sadie.

158
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:42,581
It's the best we got.

159
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:44,041
Oh, I'm not blaming you.

160
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,226
Say, what's this about the
delay?

161
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,252
How long am I booked for
this berg, do you know?

162
00:09:47,294 --> 00:09:50,756
Well, I'd compose myself
for a two week stay.

163
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:53,509
Well,
that being the case,

164
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,986
what can't be helped can't be
helped,

165
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:55,803
as the saying goes.

166
00:09:55,844 --> 00:09:56,970
That job in the field

167
00:09:57,012 --> 00:09:57,888
will keep all right, Sadie,

168
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:58,990
so I shouldn't worry about it.

169
00:09:59,014 --> 00:10:01,183
Oh, I never worry, little one.

170
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:02,392
Make the best of things today

171
00:10:02,434 --> 00:10:03,894
'cause it can't be worse
tomorrow.

172
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:07,231
Besides, I like the boys here.

173
00:10:09,316 --> 00:10:10,651
Hello, handsome.

174
00:10:10,692 --> 00:10:12,277
When did you leave Kansas?

175
00:10:13,904 --> 00:10:15,155
She got you that time, kid.

176
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,448
Shut up, you hyena.

177
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:19,243
He's very shy, Miss,
don't mind him.

178
00:10:19,284 --> 00:10:22,329
Lay off sailor, or I'll
swab the deck with you.

179
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:23,747
Ah, don't hurt him handsome.

180
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:26,125
I came from Kansas once myself,

181
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:27,751
as fast as I could hoof it.

182
00:10:29,628 --> 00:10:31,130
How are ya?

183
00:10:31,171 --> 00:10:32,381
Fine.

184
00:10:32,422 --> 00:10:33,674
Very pleased to meet a lady.

185
00:10:38,053 --> 00:10:38,846
Better look out, Miss.

186
00:10:38,887 --> 00:10:39,930
He's liable to bite.

187
00:10:40,764 --> 00:10:42,933
They act like they've had
too much oats.

188
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:44,393
Oh, she is a one.

189
00:10:44,434 --> 00:10:45,453
Lance, allow me to inform you

190
00:10:45,477 --> 00:10:47,563
that Sadie is a bit of all
right.

191
00:10:47,604 --> 00:10:49,398
Say, you'll find Sadie
some place to sleep,

192
00:10:49,439 --> 00:10:50,399
won't you, Joe?

193
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,067
With pleasure.

194
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:55,320
And now shall we discuss
our sordid business matters?

195
00:10:55,362 --> 00:10:56,572
Now you know how it is

196
00:10:56,613 --> 00:10:57,882
when you're traveling a bit
short.

197
00:10:57,906 --> 00:11:00,325
You see, Sadie left
Honolulu a bit sudden-like.

198
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,160
She's a good kid,

199
00:11:01,201 --> 00:11:02,554
although she's down on her luck
a bit.

200
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:04,955
Now, she can't pay over
a dollar a day for a room

201
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:07,499
and you've got to take care of
her from that, will you, Joe?

202
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:09,144
Yeah, I was telling
the quartermaster here

203
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:12,379
on board myself, I've got
a burner with me

204
00:11:12,421 --> 00:11:14,089
and besides, I don't eat so
much.

205
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:16,675
Oh, that'll be all right.

206
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:19,261
Mrs. Horn will take care of you.

207
00:11:19,303 --> 00:11:21,346
Well, here's bubbles.

208
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:15,067
I hear life's terrible
back home in the States now.

209
00:12:15,108 --> 00:12:16,109
How so?

210
00:12:16,151 --> 00:12:17,861
Everybody being made to
behave.

211
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:21,114
Yes, we live in the day
of the new commandment:

212
00:12:21,156 --> 00:12:23,825
Thou shalt not enjoy thyself.

213
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:26,453
I saw it coming 20 years ago.

214
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:27,996
That's why I left Chicago.

215
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:30,082
I wanted peace,

216
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,626
and I found it too.

217
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:37,381
Friend, you behold here the last
remnants

218
00:12:37,422 --> 00:12:38,924
of an Earthly paradise.

219
00:12:40,008 --> 00:12:42,261
That's my quarrel with
reformers,

220
00:12:42,302 --> 00:12:43,345
they won't let it alone.

221
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:45,597
Yes, I can readily see how a
reformer

222
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:47,683
might feel a little out of place
here.

223
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,520
Sort of like a school
marm waking up in a harem.

224
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:56,149
You remember what we were
talking about the other night?

225
00:12:56,191 --> 00:12:58,151
Have you told Dr. MacPhail yet?

226
00:12:58,193 --> 00:12:59,903
You mean about the Mallard's
customs

227
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:02,030
and the moon-dancing?

228
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:02,864
Yes.

229
00:13:02,906 --> 00:13:04,574
What did he say?

230
00:13:04,616 --> 00:13:06,243
Well, he never says very much

231
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:08,620
but I'm sure he thought
it was perfectly awful.

232
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:10,831
Now take these islanders,
doctor.

233
00:13:10,872 --> 00:13:13,667
They're naturally the
happiest, most contented

234
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:15,294
people on Earth.

235
00:13:15,335 --> 00:13:17,004
They ask nothing of life

236
00:13:17,045 --> 00:13:18,714
except to be allowed to eat,

237
00:13:18,755 --> 00:13:21,967
and sing and dance and sleep.

238
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:23,969
Thinking gives them a headache.

239
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:26,263
The trees and the sea gives
'em all the food they want

240
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:28,223
so they don't have to fight.

241
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:31,685
They're satisfied with
the gods of wind and wave.

242
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,603
Then along comes Mr.
Davidson and tells them

243
00:13:33,645 --> 00:13:36,064
they're lost souls,
they've got to be saved

244
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:37,333
whether they want to be or not.

245
00:13:37,357 --> 00:13:39,526
Too bad man couldn't
develop a soul without

246
00:13:39,568 --> 00:13:41,486
losing the Garden of Eden.

247
00:13:41,528 --> 00:13:43,113
You're a philosopher, doctor.

248
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,823
No, I just look on.

249
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:46,283
Ditto, brother.

250
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:48,285
And I guess we both see the
joke.

251
00:13:53,373 --> 00:13:56,793
And now, welcome to Villa Horn.

252
00:13:56,835 --> 00:13:58,795
He's new here and besides,

253
00:13:58,837 --> 00:13:59,963
his eyesight's bad.

254
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:01,048
Yeah, I know.

255
00:14:01,089 --> 00:14:03,467
His is bad and yours is good.

256
00:14:03,508 --> 00:14:06,219
But mine's better and I'm taking
handsome.

257
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:08,740
You boys can pick up those
packages

258
00:14:08,764 --> 00:14:10,265
and tag along in back if you
like,

259
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:11,683
but don't get run over.

260
00:14:13,685 --> 00:14:15,312
That's done it.

261
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,146
The jackass said,

262
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:18,190
"No, not now, it's too hot,

263
00:14:18,231 --> 00:14:20,609
but in the cool of the
evening, I'll be there."

264
00:14:23,111 --> 00:14:25,197
Moses on a mountaintop,

265
00:14:25,238 --> 00:14:27,366
so this is the sunny South Seas.

266
00:14:27,407 --> 00:14:28,784
What a place.

267
00:14:28,825 --> 00:14:30,702
Nothing but quiet and mud.

268
00:14:31,953 --> 00:14:34,039
Farewell, pretty ones.

269
00:14:34,081 --> 00:14:35,290
Farewell.

270
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:37,793
You ain't looked like that
since our first auto ride.

271
00:14:38,877 --> 00:14:41,546
Take that stuff and put
it down anywhere, boys.

272
00:14:41,588 --> 00:14:43,608
Well, I guess my idea of
me looking neat and chipper

273
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,342
when I get to Apia is shot.

274
00:14:45,384 --> 00:14:47,219
I shouldn't worry about that,
Sadie.

275
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:50,013
With all this heat, you'll soon
be as dry as a blotting pad.

276
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,935
That's I should worry in Jap,
buttercup.

277
00:14:56,561 --> 00:14:58,146
Mrs. MacPhaill,
tomorrow you and I

278
00:14:58,188 --> 00:14:59,856
must sew the mosquito netting

279
00:14:59,898 --> 00:15:01,775
or the nights will be
unendurable.

280
00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:03,026
Why not sew them today?

281
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:05,153
I have no fancy for
being eaten up tonight.

282
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:08,865
I prefer not to do any
sewing on the Sabbath.

283
00:15:08,907 --> 00:15:12,119
It would be different if
one were indecently exposed

284
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,287
by a tear in one's clothing, for
instance.

285
00:15:14,329 --> 00:15:15,580
But under the circumstances,

286
00:15:15,622 --> 00:15:18,750
it might be a very bad
example for the natives.

287
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,355
I suppose I'll find it
pretty slow down at Apia,

288
00:15:22,379 --> 00:15:23,839
won't I, grandpa?

289
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,525
Things ought to
brighten up considerable,

290
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:26,550
after you get there.

291
00:15:26,591 --> 00:15:29,094
Oh, Mr. Horn.

292
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,282
Say, I'd have thought
you'd been thirsty enough

293
00:15:33,306 --> 00:15:34,558
to locate it by instinct.

294
00:15:34,599 --> 00:15:35,392
Here, I'll look.

295
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:37,644
There's the shy Kentucky
refugee.

296
00:15:39,312 --> 00:15:42,607
Who's got a corkscrew?

297
00:15:42,649 --> 00:15:43,775
Here you are, Sadie.

298
00:15:46,361 --> 00:15:47,487
Thanks, baldie.

299
00:15:51,032 --> 00:15:52,451
Well boys, let's dip the beak.

300
00:15:52,492 --> 00:15:54,995
Well, now, ain't that a
beautiful sight?

301
00:15:55,036 --> 00:15:56,705
After you lots, delight in me
gizzard.

302
00:15:56,746 --> 00:15:58,224
I'll find a glass
for you, Miss Thompson.

303
00:15:58,248 --> 00:16:00,167
What for? Down the hatch.

304
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:03,170
Now there's a lady after me
own heart.

305
00:16:03,211 --> 00:16:04,004
Friend of mine slipped me that

306
00:16:04,045 --> 00:16:05,172
just before I left Honolulu.

307
00:16:05,213 --> 00:16:06,816
"Not that you'll need it,
Sadie," said he.

308
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,467
And right he was, Sadie.

309
00:16:08,508 --> 00:16:10,802
You're not the type to
need hooch to pep you up.

310
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:12,304
Ah, I was born hooched.

311
00:16:12,345 --> 00:16:13,472
Holy moly, look at this.

312
00:16:13,513 --> 00:16:15,390
The Wabash Blues.

313
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:17,184
Music and a nip of liquor,

314
00:16:17,225 --> 00:16:19,853
that's what a rainy day is for,
says I.

315
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:21,646
Can you dance, handsome?

316
00:16:21,688 --> 00:16:22,731
No, Miss Thompson.

317
00:16:22,772 --> 00:16:25,233
I'm a clubfoot, I never
could twist my legs right.

318
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,110
Well, I'll learn you before I
leave,

319
00:16:27,152 --> 00:16:28,152
that's a threat.

320
00:16:28,945 --> 00:16:30,631
Quartermaster here is
a great little stepper.

321
00:16:30,655 --> 00:16:32,616
You ought to see him shake a
shoulder.

322
00:16:32,657 --> 00:16:36,119
For one of these brains in
here, you'd be surprised.

323
00:16:36,161 --> 00:16:36,953
Come on, Ethelbert,

324
00:16:36,995 --> 00:16:38,222
let's show these island boys how

325
00:16:38,246 --> 00:16:40,582
hip meets hip in the
gay cafes of Honolulu.

326
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:42,918
Right-oh, let's have
a go at it.

327
00:16:42,959 --> 00:16:44,628
Here, mark my cabbage.

328
00:16:44,669 --> 00:16:46,046
Now, nothing too fancy now.

329
00:16:46,087 --> 00:16:47,172
No.

330
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:56,723
Shake that thing, baby.

331
00:16:56,765 --> 00:16:58,934
Shake that thing.

332
00:16:58,975 --> 00:17:01,269
Hot mama, burn my clothes.

333
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:06,483
Pick them up nice
and put them down easy.

334
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:07,525
That's it.

335
00:17:08,902 --> 00:17:10,111
That's the stuff, Batesy.

336
00:17:10,153 --> 00:17:11,154
Now get the high five.

337
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,531
It isn't the rhythm that
counts,

338
00:17:12,572 --> 00:17:13,490
it's the motion.

339
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:15,742
Come on now, glide.

340
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:17,285
Attaboy.

341
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,370
Young woman.

342
00:17:18,411 --> 00:17:19,829
You got the swing now, baby.

343
00:17:19,871 --> 00:17:22,707
Young woman, have you no
respect for the Lord's day?

344
00:17:22,749 --> 00:17:23,542
What?

345
00:17:23,583 --> 00:17:24,918
This is Sunday, young woman.

346
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,127
Were you speaking to me?

347
00:17:26,169 --> 00:17:29,172
I am simply reminding you
that this is the Sabbath.

348
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:31,800
Sabbath? Yesterday was
Saturday, right you are.

349
00:17:31,841 --> 00:17:33,552
I say, this must stop.

350
00:17:33,593 --> 00:17:34,594
Do you hear me?

351
00:17:36,304 --> 00:17:37,973
I say ma'am, are we disturbing
you?

352
00:17:38,014 --> 00:17:39,599
Whether I am being disturbed
or not

353
00:17:39,641 --> 00:17:41,142
is of no consequence.

354
00:17:41,184 --> 00:17:42,537
There's six days in the week to
dance

355
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:44,271
if you must dance.

356
00:17:44,312 --> 00:17:48,316
Mr. Horn, is this sort of
thing general in your store?

357
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,068
Well, it's a general store
ma'am.

358
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,861
Oh, enough said.

359
00:17:51,903 --> 00:17:53,029
Complaints registered.

360
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:55,615
Let's go to my private suite

361
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,784
if you've no objection, Mr.
Horn.

362
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,579
No objection as far as I'm
concerned.

363
00:18:00,620 --> 00:18:01,913
Come on, Ethelbert.

364
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:04,958
Come on boys, we're moving.

365
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,792
You bring the records, handsome.

366
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:06,834
And you, the hooch.

367
00:18:07,752 --> 00:18:09,438
Drop in later if you
feel like it, Mr. Horn.

368
00:18:09,462 --> 00:18:10,630
Always glad to see you.

369
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:14,384
Who is that young woman?

370
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:17,554
Her name, ma'am, is
Thompson as far as I know.

371
00:18:17,596 --> 00:18:19,598
I mean, what is she?

372
00:18:19,639 --> 00:18:21,558
I didn't inquire.

373
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,976
She was on the Arduna,
wasn't she?

374
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,936
I'm aware she was.

375
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:30,900
I'm afraid Mr. Davidson
will not like this at all.

376
00:18:36,114 --> 00:18:37,341
I've argued it out with the
governor

377
00:18:37,365 --> 00:18:38,950
but there's nothing to be done.

378
00:18:38,992 --> 00:18:41,202
That means 10 days here.

379
00:18:41,244 --> 00:18:42,746
Two weeks probably.

380
00:18:42,787 --> 00:18:43,973
Well, I've prepared for the
worst

381
00:18:43,997 --> 00:18:46,625
and taken rooms for us upstairs.

382
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,919
Two weeks with nothing to occupy
us.

383
00:18:49,961 --> 00:18:51,212
Let's enforce an activity

384
00:18:51,254 --> 00:18:52,589
that's likely to prove
wearisome.

385
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:54,431
The only thing to do is
to portion out the day

386
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:56,343
to different occupations.

387
00:18:56,384 --> 00:18:57,594
Certain hours of the day,

388
00:18:57,636 --> 00:18:59,262
we will set aside for study.

389
00:18:59,304 --> 00:19:03,016
Certain hours for exercise,
rain or shine.

390
00:19:03,058 --> 00:19:06,853
And too, certain hours
will go for recreation.

391
00:19:06,895 --> 00:19:08,688
Recreation may be
hard to find.

392
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,082
Someone appears
to have found it.

393
00:19:10,106 --> 00:19:12,233
It's a person from
the 2nd class,

394
00:19:12,275 --> 00:19:13,943
exceedingly common.

395
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:16,154
Very flashily dressed.

396
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:19,157
In fact, she looks rather fast
to me.

397
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:21,826
Perhaps you noticed her on the
boat.

398
00:19:21,868 --> 00:19:22,827
I met her.

399
00:19:22,869 --> 00:19:24,746
Rather a good-natured
girl while we're waiting

400
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:25,830
for a position on Apia.

401
00:19:25,872 --> 00:19:26,706
What kind of a girl?

402
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:28,375
Oh, just an ordinary human
being,

403
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:30,335
not over-prosperous,
I should say.

404
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,003
I think it's perfectly
outrageous

405
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:33,439
for her to keep that music up,
don't you?

406
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,173
If she wishes to play her own
machine,

407
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:37,217
it's not our right to interfere.

408
00:19:37,258 --> 00:19:38,301
By the way, doctor,

409
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:39,928
we can visit the Naval hospital
tomorrow

410
00:19:39,969 --> 00:19:40,762
if you think it would
interest you.

411
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:43,306
It's a busman's holiday,
but I'll go.

412
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:48,978
The Arduna must be going
out before her scheduled time.

413
00:19:50,021 --> 00:19:51,064
I hate to see her go.

414
00:19:51,106 --> 00:19:53,525
She seemed to be our last link
with home.

415
00:19:53,566 --> 00:19:57,195
So long-

416
00:19:57,237 --> 00:19:58,154
You better hurry, love,

417
00:19:58,196 --> 00:19:59,280
or you're gonna get licked.

418
00:19:59,322 --> 00:20:01,700
Right-oh Sadie, I'm sorry
I can't stay for lunch

419
00:20:01,741 --> 00:20:02,534
but I'm off.

420
00:20:02,575 --> 00:20:04,053
But I hopes I'll see you again
sometime

421
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:05,995
because you're a good kid
and I likes you.

422
00:20:06,037 --> 00:20:06,830
I'll tell you what you do,

423
00:20:06,871 --> 00:20:09,374
you write me a nice little
loving postcard, will you?

424
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,127
Right-oh, a nice little
postcard.

425
00:20:12,168 --> 00:20:13,044
And once you write it,

426
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:14,129
just drop it in the ocean.

427
00:20:15,463 --> 00:20:16,423
Well, bye-bye.

428
00:20:16,464 --> 00:20:17,257
Toodle-ooh.

429
00:20:17,298 --> 00:20:19,592
- Aloha.
- Sayonara.

430
00:20:19,634 --> 00:20:20,634
I'm off.

431
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:29,269
Goodbye, Mr. Davidson.

432
00:20:35,608 --> 00:20:36,943
Goodbye, Mr. Davidson.

433
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:44,451
Goodbye, Mr. Davidson.

434
00:20:48,496 --> 00:20:50,498
Hello, Mr. Davidson.

435
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:52,560
You better get aboard,
Quartermaster,

436
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:54,002
as fast as you can.

437
00:20:54,043 --> 00:20:56,671
Right-oh, well,
goodbye everybody.

438
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:58,089
Bye-bye, folks.

439
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:14,439
Goodbye, Mr. Davidson.

440
00:21:14,481 --> 00:21:17,108
Come on, the tea's
getting cold.

441
00:21:30,997 --> 00:21:32,332
How long has this
been going on?

442
00:21:32,373 --> 00:21:33,583
All morning.

443
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:34,977
Where did those Marines
come from?

444
00:21:35,001 --> 00:21:38,004
They just appeared
from nowhere in her wake.

445
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:40,024
If we're to have a fortnight
of this sort of thing,

446
00:21:40,048 --> 00:21:41,257
I don't know what we shall all

447
00:21:41,299 --> 00:21:43,134
feel like at the end of it.

448
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:45,845
What's the matter, Alfred?

449
00:21:45,887 --> 00:21:47,072
Of course, it just occurred
to me.

450
00:21:47,096 --> 00:21:48,890
The woman is out of Evolay.

451
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:50,576
The thought occurred to
me when I first saw her

452
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,143
but I didn't dare speak of it.

453
00:21:52,185 --> 00:21:53,603
What's Evolay?

454
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:56,397
The plague spot of Honolulu.

455
00:21:56,439 --> 00:21:57,816
That long-haired guy in there

456
00:21:57,857 --> 00:22:00,610
just gave me the filthiest look.

457
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:02,153
What are you going to do,
Alfred?

458
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:02,987
What do you expect me to do?

459
00:22:03,029 --> 00:22:05,240
I'm not going to have this
house turned into a brothel.

460
00:22:05,281 --> 00:22:06,074
I'm going to stop it.

461
00:22:06,115 --> 00:22:07,301
She has a number of men
in there,

462
00:22:07,325 --> 00:22:08,785
isn't it rather rash
to go in now?

463
00:22:08,827 --> 00:22:11,287
You know Mr. Davidson
very little

464
00:22:11,329 --> 00:22:13,832
if you think that fear
of physical danger

465
00:22:13,873 --> 00:22:16,584
is going to stop him in the
performance of his duties.

466
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:20,088
Stop. This has gone
far enough.

467
00:22:21,589 --> 00:22:23,842
- Hey!
- Boys, the skids.

468
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:28,847
The next time, I'll get sore.

469
00:22:28,888 --> 00:22:31,140
They'll be no next time.

470
00:22:31,182 --> 00:22:32,684
When you bust into a lady's
room,

471
00:22:32,725 --> 00:22:35,103
you ought to get someone
to introduce you, fella.

472
00:22:36,646 --> 00:22:37,981
Fall in, sweetheart.

473
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:42,485
Alfred.

474
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:43,527
Alfred.

475
00:22:48,741 --> 00:22:51,160
I don't know what he'll do.

476
00:22:51,202 --> 00:22:54,414
All I know is I wouldn't
be in that girl's shoes

477
00:22:54,455 --> 00:22:55,748
for anything in the world.

478
00:23:46,799 --> 00:23:48,134
Hello, there.

479
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:48,968
Hello.

480
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:50,094
Been out for a walk?

481
00:23:50,136 --> 00:23:54,807
About two steps, it's like
walking through hot pea soup.

482
00:23:54,849 --> 00:23:56,976
What time of day is it?

483
00:23:57,018 --> 00:24:00,521
Going on six, a whole hour
to put in before dinner.

484
00:24:00,563 --> 00:24:01,731
Been to the hospital today?

485
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:04,776
No, Davidson's too busy.

486
00:24:04,817 --> 00:24:07,403
Nothing left to do but twiddle
my thumbs.

487
00:24:07,445 --> 00:24:09,197
Why twiddle?

488
00:24:09,238 --> 00:24:11,157
Forced idleness
makes them restless.

489
00:24:12,992 --> 00:24:15,662
Back in Illinois,
where I was raised,

490
00:24:15,703 --> 00:24:17,622
it was generally believed
that a person

491
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:19,082
who stayed away from business

492
00:24:19,123 --> 00:24:22,418
more than one working
day in every 10 years,

493
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:25,588
was a loose, dangerous,
and depraved character.

494
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:32,345
You don't see a bottle around
here anywhere, do you Doc?

495
00:24:34,222 --> 00:24:35,222
Have a drink.

496
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:39,018
Not just now.

497
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,979
Well the offer still holds.

498
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:42,730
There's more in the store.

499
00:24:42,772 --> 00:24:43,690
Now what was I saying?

500
00:24:43,731 --> 00:24:46,609
The subject I believe was
the evil of too much work.

501
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:48,236
So it was.

502
00:24:48,277 --> 00:24:50,279
There's a lot too much
misdirected energy

503
00:24:50,321 --> 00:24:51,280
in this world, doctor.

504
00:24:51,322 --> 00:24:52,949
Are you speaking
biographically

505
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,283
or autobiographically?

506
00:24:54,325 --> 00:24:55,868
Confidentially.

507
00:24:55,910 --> 00:24:58,162
That was a mighty foolish
thing Davidson did.

508
00:24:59,414 --> 00:25:00,498
That girl, Sadie Thompson,

509
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:01,916
wasn't doing any harm.

510
00:25:01,958 --> 00:25:03,543
Hmm, I see what you're
getting at.

511
00:25:03,584 --> 00:25:05,504
He's been after me for
letting her have a room.

512
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:06,379
It's your own house, isn't it?

513
00:25:06,421 --> 00:25:10,049
Yes, but people like that
have got a lot of influence.

514
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:12,051
Once they get down on a traitor,

515
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:14,053
he might as well set up shop
and quit.

516
00:25:14,095 --> 00:25:15,680
Surely he isn't asking you
to turn

517
00:25:15,722 --> 00:25:17,306
this poor girl out
into the rain.

518
00:25:17,348 --> 00:25:18,808
No, not exactly.

519
00:25:19,642 --> 00:25:21,686
He knows there'd be no place for
her to go

520
00:25:21,728 --> 00:25:22,520
except a native hut.

521
00:25:22,562 --> 00:25:25,231
Not but what I think she'd
do better to go to one

522
00:25:25,273 --> 00:25:27,775
than stay here, now that he's
on to her.

523
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:29,086
Just what does he want you
to do?

524
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:32,530
Well, he said he wanted
to be fair to her and to me,

525
00:25:32,572 --> 00:25:34,699
but he wouldn't stand for any
doings.

526
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:35,575
What do you think, Horn?

527
00:25:35,616 --> 00:25:37,368
Is she out of Evolay,

528
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:38,703
that Honolulu place?

529
00:25:38,745 --> 00:25:40,747
I don't know and I don't care.

530
00:25:40,788 --> 00:25:42,331
What if she is?

531
00:25:42,373 --> 00:25:45,543
We've all crossed thresholds
we don't brag about.

532
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:02,351
Hello doctor.

533
00:26:02,393 --> 00:26:03,393
Evening.

534
00:26:06,481 --> 00:26:07,481
Evening, Joe.

535
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:11,402
My, the merry water sprites
sure do carry on, don't they?

536
00:26:11,444 --> 00:26:12,445
Why I-

537
00:26:12,487 --> 00:26:13,988
- Ah, let's don't mention the
heat.

538
00:26:14,864 --> 00:26:16,491
I just got around to
get myself dressed

539
00:26:16,532 --> 00:26:18,242
and it's almost time to
go to bed.

540
00:26:19,202 --> 00:26:20,554
I been playing solitaire all
afternoon,

541
00:26:20,578 --> 00:26:23,039
trying to decide what to have
for supper.

542
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:25,166
Tuna fish or beans.

543
00:26:25,208 --> 00:26:26,667
And beans won.

544
00:26:28,127 --> 00:26:30,004
Then I played beans against
tamales,

545
00:26:30,046 --> 00:26:31,089
just for something to do

546
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:32,840
and tamales got the set.

547
00:26:32,882 --> 00:26:34,550
Got any canned tamales,
Mr. Horn?

548
00:26:34,592 --> 00:26:35,510
I guess so.

549
00:26:35,551 --> 00:26:37,470
Poke around until you find them.

550
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,599
Oh, no hurry.

551
00:26:41,641 --> 00:26:42,641
Lots of time.

552
00:26:44,018 --> 00:26:46,145
There's so much time lying
loose around this island,

553
00:26:46,187 --> 00:26:47,706
somebody ought to bottle
it up and send it back

554
00:26:47,730 --> 00:26:48,815
where they need some.

555
00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:51,984
You don't mind, do you,

556
00:26:52,026 --> 00:26:53,253
seeing we're here all by
ourselves,

557
00:26:53,277 --> 00:26:55,363
if I sit down and have
a skag with you boys?

558
00:26:55,404 --> 00:26:56,197
Not at all.

559
00:26:56,239 --> 00:26:57,031
Have a drink.

560
00:26:57,073 --> 00:26:58,073
Thanks.

561
00:27:00,284 --> 00:27:01,845
You haven't seen that
Marine Sergeant around

562
00:27:01,869 --> 00:27:03,371
that I call Handsome, have you?

563
00:27:03,412 --> 00:27:05,790
No, he hasn't been
around today.

564
00:27:07,667 --> 00:27:09,210
Oh, it don't matter.

565
00:27:09,252 --> 00:27:10,920
I just want to ask him
something.

566
00:27:11,754 --> 00:27:12,547
If you do see him,

567
00:27:12,588 --> 00:27:14,674
tell him to drop around
this evening, will you?

568
00:27:14,715 --> 00:27:16,843
You know what I said
to you last night,

569
00:27:16,884 --> 00:27:19,095
as friend to friend, get me.

570
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:21,681
I'd go slow on company
for a day or two.

571
00:27:22,598 --> 00:27:23,516
I see,

572
00:27:23,558 --> 00:27:26,227
until Davidson gets over his
terrible experience, huh?

573
00:27:27,478 --> 00:27:29,730
Do you think I've been to
blame for what happened?

574
00:27:29,772 --> 00:27:31,107
I ain't blaming anyone.

575
00:27:31,149 --> 00:27:32,543
Pushing himself in on us
that way.

576
00:27:32,567 --> 00:27:34,360
What harm were we doing?

577
00:27:34,402 --> 00:27:36,028
Just talking and singing,

578
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:37,488
not a word or thought out
of the way

579
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:39,448
when bang goes the door and
in he comes,

580
00:27:39,490 --> 00:27:41,033
knocking the phonograph over.

581
00:27:41,075 --> 00:27:43,077
"Here," I says, "quit that."

582
00:27:43,119 --> 00:27:44,370
Then he began to bawl us out.

583
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:46,581
Well, the boys naturally
thought he'd gone crazy

584
00:27:46,622 --> 00:27:47,957
so they put the skids under him.

585
00:27:47,999 --> 00:27:49,041
I know.

586
00:27:49,083 --> 00:27:51,085
Anyway, I wouldn't attract
his attention anymore

587
00:27:51,127 --> 00:27:52,628
than I had to just now.

588
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:55,089
Well, if it comes
to that,

589
00:27:55,131 --> 00:27:57,008
he better not attract mine.

590
00:27:57,049 --> 00:27:58,318
I've never known anyone like him

591
00:27:58,342 --> 00:27:59,343
and I don't want to.

592
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:06,100
Say, what kind of an egg is
the governor of this place,

593
00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:06,934
do you know?

594
00:28:06,976 --> 00:28:08,561
- The governor?
- Yeah.

595
00:28:08,603 --> 00:28:09,896
Let's see,

596
00:28:09,937 --> 00:28:11,606
oh, a pretty good sort I'd say.

597
00:28:11,647 --> 00:28:12,647
Why?

598
00:28:13,649 --> 00:28:14,859
Oh nothing.

599
00:28:14,901 --> 00:28:16,611
I just wanted to know, that's
all.

600
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,447
The nerve of him,

601
00:28:19,488 --> 00:28:21,657
going to see the governor
about me.

602
00:28:21,699 --> 00:28:22,885
Did you ever hear
the like of it?

603
00:28:22,909 --> 00:28:24,511
How do you know he went
to see him about you?

604
00:28:24,535 --> 00:28:25,953
O'Hara told me.

605
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:28,414
He's reported O'Hara to
his officer for drinking.

606
00:28:29,415 --> 00:28:31,500
I don't want that boy to
get any trouble through me.

607
00:28:31,542 --> 00:28:34,128
Oh, I guess O'Hara can
take care of hisself.

608
00:28:34,170 --> 00:28:36,464
Yeah, well so can I if it
comes to that.

609
00:28:36,505 --> 00:28:37,965
Miss Thompson, I'd be careful.

610
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:38,799
Of what?

611
00:28:38,841 --> 00:28:40,927
I'd be careful for my own
good.

612
00:28:40,968 --> 00:28:42,220
You can't tell.

613
00:28:43,137 --> 00:28:45,306
Give me strength.

614
00:28:45,348 --> 00:28:46,575
How many times have
I got to tell you

615
00:28:46,599 --> 00:28:48,768
that old sin-buster
don't mean a thing to me?

616
00:28:48,809 --> 00:28:50,811
If he minds his own
business, I'll mind mine.

617
00:28:50,853 --> 00:28:52,271
And if he's looking for trouble,

618
00:28:52,313 --> 00:28:54,565
I'll see that he gets it,
that's all.

619
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:56,734
Mr. Davidson's opinion
of people

620
00:28:56,776 --> 00:28:59,528
- is never wrong.
- Oh, really?

621
00:29:01,572 --> 00:29:03,199
Me thinks I hear
the winds of reform

622
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:04,617
whistling down the chimney.

623
00:29:05,534 --> 00:29:08,621
Swear after low hussy frolics
off to buy her supper.

624
00:29:11,707 --> 00:29:13,477
Where do you keep your
canned tamales, old partner?

625
00:29:13,501 --> 00:29:14,293
If there's any left,

626
00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:16,420
you'll find them on
that shelf by the door.

627
00:29:23,219 --> 00:29:25,429
Anyway, there's no ill
feeling between any of us,

628
00:29:25,471 --> 00:29:27,014
- is there?
- Huh?

629
00:29:27,056 --> 00:29:29,809
Well, I wouldn't say the
doc has been exactly chatty.

630
00:29:32,979 --> 00:29:35,982
Life just teems with quiet fun.

631
00:29:39,694 --> 00:29:41,529
Has Mr. Davidson returned yet?

632
00:29:41,570 --> 00:29:42,863
Not yet, Mrs. Davidson.

633
00:29:42,905 --> 00:29:44,007
How's the headache, any better?

634
00:29:44,031 --> 00:29:45,449
Very little.

635
00:29:54,625 --> 00:29:56,544
That girl, Miss Thompson.

636
00:29:56,585 --> 00:29:58,921
I have an idea she's
sorry for what happened.

637
00:29:59,922 --> 00:30:01,882
If she knew what
she'd really done,

638
00:30:01,924 --> 00:30:03,551
she'd be sorrier still.

639
00:30:04,719 --> 00:30:07,471
Mr. Davidson has a wonderful
heart

640
00:30:07,513 --> 00:30:09,974
and no one has ever gone
to him in trouble

641
00:30:10,016 --> 00:30:12,101
without being comforted,

642
00:30:12,143 --> 00:30:14,395
but he has no mercy for sin.

643
00:30:14,437 --> 00:30:16,439
Did you find your tamales,
Sadie?

644
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:18,024
Yeah.

645
00:30:18,065 --> 00:30:20,067
Don't look around,
here she comes now.

646
00:30:21,485 --> 00:30:22,611
Yes, here I come now.

647
00:30:22,653 --> 00:30:24,113
Why shouldn't I come now?

648
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:25,740
See here, let's settle this.

649
00:30:25,781 --> 00:30:27,050
I'm paying for my own room here,

650
00:30:27,074 --> 00:30:28,200
isn't that so, Mr. Horn?

651
00:30:28,242 --> 00:30:29,368
That's so, Miss Thompson.

652
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:30,470
Will you kindly tell
your guests then

653
00:30:30,494 --> 00:30:32,496
that I have just as much
right here as they have?

654
00:30:32,538 --> 00:30:35,458
Now, Miss Thompson, there
isn't anyone saying you haven't.

655
00:30:35,499 --> 00:30:36,709
Don't look at her.

656
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:37,835
Don't speak to her.

657
00:30:40,838 --> 00:30:42,798
No, I wouldn't if I was you.

658
00:30:50,514 --> 00:30:53,351
She's brazen, outrageous.

659
00:30:53,392 --> 00:30:55,519
Don't, you'll only harm
yourself.

660
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,147
Oh, it's foolish, I know,

661
00:30:59,148 --> 00:31:01,400
but it's the first time
I've ever had words

662
00:31:01,442 --> 00:31:03,361
with a woman of that sort.

663
00:31:05,154 --> 00:31:06,405
Well, there's one comfort.

664
00:31:06,447 --> 00:31:09,658
We shan't have to suffer this
sort of thing much longer.

665
00:31:10,576 --> 00:31:13,037
Mr. Davidson is
attending to that.

666
00:31:18,709 --> 00:31:19,709
Hello, Davidson.

667
00:31:20,836 --> 00:31:23,422
Alfred, please change
your wet clothes.

668
00:31:23,464 --> 00:31:25,341
No, I shall be going
out again, probably.

669
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:26,467
Again?

670
00:31:26,509 --> 00:31:29,387
Oh, Alfred, you must try
to get a little rest.

671
00:31:29,428 --> 00:31:30,763
Alfred, you must.

672
00:31:30,805 --> 00:31:32,598
My wife like Martha,

673
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,475
thou has troubled
thyself about many things

674
00:31:34,517 --> 00:31:36,560
but mostly about me.

675
00:31:36,602 --> 00:31:38,038
I do not know what I should ever
have done

676
00:31:38,062 --> 00:31:39,688
without my dear wife.

677
00:31:39,730 --> 00:31:41,440
Merely days of our island work,

678
00:31:41,482 --> 00:31:43,234
it was she who gave me
the strength

679
00:31:43,275 --> 00:31:44,318
and courage to go on.

680
00:31:46,737 --> 00:31:47,863
Alfred,

681
00:31:47,905 --> 00:31:51,450
just before you got back,
that girl spoke to me.

682
00:31:51,492 --> 00:31:53,869
She jeered and screamed at us.

683
00:31:53,911 --> 00:31:56,038
What are you going to do
about it?

684
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,432
Dinner ready.

685
00:31:57,456 --> 00:31:59,417
Strange how one's thoughts
run to food

686
00:31:59,458 --> 00:32:01,085
when there's nothing else
to think of.

687
00:32:01,127 --> 00:32:03,629
As it happens, there is
a great deal to think of.

688
00:32:03,671 --> 00:32:05,506
This Thompson woman,
you say, spoke to you?

689
00:32:05,548 --> 00:32:07,842
Yes, she thrust herself in
upon us

690
00:32:07,883 --> 00:32:08,884
with low insults.

691
00:32:08,926 --> 00:32:10,553
Hmm, the governor tells me

692
00:32:10,594 --> 00:32:12,930
that the affair is no concern of
his,

693
00:32:12,972 --> 00:32:14,598
but if I find her incorrigible,

694
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,851
I shall see to it that he acts.

695
00:32:16,892 --> 00:32:18,310
I'm afraid he has no backbone.

696
00:32:18,352 --> 00:32:20,354
I suppose that means he won't
do exactly

697
00:32:20,396 --> 00:32:22,440
as you want, whatever it
is you want him to do.

698
00:32:22,481 --> 00:32:24,108
I only want him to do
what is right.

699
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:26,902
There may be differences of
opinion as to what is right.

700
00:32:26,944 --> 00:32:28,821
If a man had
a gangrenous foot,

701
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:30,239
would you have patience
with anyone

702
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:31,740
who hesitates to cut it off?

703
00:32:31,782 --> 00:32:33,742
Gangrene is a matter of fact.

704
00:32:33,784 --> 00:32:35,035
And is not evil?

705
00:32:35,077 --> 00:32:37,246
To me, it's always
seemed a matter of opinion.

706
00:32:37,288 --> 00:32:38,914
Anyway, the poor thing
will only be here

707
00:32:38,956 --> 00:32:40,541
until the boat for Apia goes.

708
00:32:40,583 --> 00:32:41,685
And after she gets to Apia?

709
00:32:41,709 --> 00:32:43,627
I can't see how that
concerns us.

710
00:32:43,669 --> 00:32:45,063
Well, that's where
you and I differ doctor.

711
00:32:45,087 --> 00:32:47,548
I think it'll be best if I spoke
to her.

712
00:32:47,590 --> 00:32:49,758
But Alfred, why do you
see her?

713
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:52,303
I cannot act until I have
given her every chance.

714
00:32:52,344 --> 00:32:53,971
She'll only insult you.

715
00:32:54,013 --> 00:32:54,805
Let her insult me.

716
00:32:54,847 --> 00:32:55,764
Let her spit on me.

717
00:32:55,806 --> 00:32:57,725
She has an immortal soul

718
00:32:57,766 --> 00:33:00,311
and I must do all in my power
to save it.

719
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:13,699
Miss Thompson,
I want to talk to you.

720
00:33:13,741 --> 00:33:15,242
I'm eating my supper.

721
00:33:15,284 --> 00:33:16,827
I'll wait until you're
through.

722
00:33:16,869 --> 00:33:20,164
Oh, I guess the supper can
stand by if it's important.

723
00:33:37,223 --> 00:33:39,308
Miss Thompson, I have
come to make you a gift,

724
00:33:39,350 --> 00:33:41,936
the most precious gift
that life can offer.

725
00:33:44,021 --> 00:33:45,439
You want to give me something?

726
00:33:45,481 --> 00:33:46,982
Yes, I want to give you
something.

727
00:33:48,150 --> 00:33:49,485
I guess I'm not following.

728
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:50,861
The gift I offer is free.

729
00:33:55,866 --> 00:33:56,659
I don't know why I get

730
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:58,661
all this attention from you,
Mr. Davidson.

731
00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:01,539
I guess you mean well.

732
00:34:02,998 --> 00:34:04,124
I think I can worry along

733
00:34:04,166 --> 00:34:07,127
as I've been worrying along
for these several years.

734
00:34:07,169 --> 00:34:09,880
I've gone my own way and
don't ask any favors.

735
00:34:09,922 --> 00:34:11,775
Those who have the key
of salvation offered them

736
00:34:11,799 --> 00:34:13,217
and failed to open the door

737
00:34:13,259 --> 00:34:14,510
must be destroyed.

738
00:34:15,928 --> 00:34:16,720
Oh, I see what you mean

739
00:34:16,762 --> 00:34:19,098
but I won't get destroyed.

740
00:34:19,139 --> 00:34:20,975
I always make out one way
or another.

741
00:34:24,103 --> 00:34:25,121
If that's all, Mr. Davidson,

742
00:34:25,145 --> 00:34:26,272
I'll go on eating.

743
00:34:26,313 --> 00:34:27,439
I'm hungry.

744
00:34:27,481 --> 00:34:29,084
You're hungry for the
bread of the spirit.

745
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:32,194
You're thirsty for the
waters of eternal life.

746
00:34:33,404 --> 00:34:35,030
- You mean right by me, Mr.
- Davidson,

747
00:34:35,072 --> 00:34:36,490
and I'm grateful,

748
00:34:36,532 --> 00:34:39,285
especially after what
happened the other day.

749
00:34:39,326 --> 00:34:42,413
You know, just between
ourselves,

750
00:34:43,289 --> 00:34:44,724
I had a feeling you were laying
to get me

751
00:34:44,748 --> 00:34:46,292
for that little trouble we had.

752
00:34:47,293 --> 00:34:48,377
I felt awful bad about it

753
00:34:48,419 --> 00:34:50,379
and I've been wanting to
apologize.

754
00:34:50,421 --> 00:34:51,380
I see you are mistaking me

755
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:53,632
but I do not think willfully.

756
00:34:53,674 --> 00:34:56,218
They all said you were sore
but,

757
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:57,696
well, I didn't think a man
as big as you

758
00:34:57,720 --> 00:34:59,531
could hold a grudge over
a little misunderstanding.

759
00:34:59,555 --> 00:35:01,640
This is all beside the
point, Miss Thompson.

760
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:03,642
The thing that concerns me now

761
00:35:03,684 --> 00:35:05,936
is that you be given
your chance before I act.

762
00:35:07,688 --> 00:35:08,480
My chance for what?

763
00:35:08,522 --> 00:35:09,982
Your chance to be saved.

764
00:35:13,861 --> 00:35:15,529
Oh, I'm all right.

765
00:35:17,031 --> 00:35:18,574
Don't you worry about me a bit.

766
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:22,911
You see, I'm a happy go
lucky sort of a fella.

767
00:35:22,953 --> 00:35:24,455
It's true, I'm broke now

768
00:35:24,496 --> 00:35:25,914
but that don't worry me.

769
00:35:25,956 --> 00:35:27,601
I'll be all right as
soon as I get to Apia.

770
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,668
I've got friends there.

771
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:31,587
Yes, what sort of friends?

772
00:35:32,713 --> 00:35:33,713
Just friends.

773
00:35:35,174 --> 00:35:36,634
Girl I used to work with is
there

774
00:35:36,675 --> 00:35:39,637
and some American boys have
opened up a sugar plant.

775
00:35:39,678 --> 00:35:41,358
She wrote me I could
have a job as cashier.

776
00:35:41,388 --> 00:35:42,640
I'm pretty quick at figures.

777
00:35:42,681 --> 00:35:45,351
For some time, you've lived
in Honolulu, haven't you?

778
00:35:45,392 --> 00:35:47,519
What did you do there?

779
00:35:47,561 --> 00:35:48,354
I had a job.

780
00:35:48,395 --> 00:35:49,563
What kind of a job?

781
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:53,067
Well, part of the time

782
00:35:53,108 --> 00:35:54,485
I had sort of a singing job.

783
00:35:55,694 --> 00:35:57,738
My voice ain't so bad if
you don't listen too hard.

784
00:35:57,780 --> 00:35:59,198
Before you went away to
Honolulu,

785
00:35:59,239 --> 00:36:00,239
where were you?

786
00:36:00,991 --> 00:36:02,135
Where did I come from, do you
