1044
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:41,988
me throwing the rice.

1045
00:45:42,030 --> 00:45:44,449
I'll bet
you'll be glad to see him.

1046
00:45:44,491 --> 00:45:45,951
If you should go to Sydney,

1047
00:45:45,992 --> 00:45:49,162
Lefty and Maggie will
put you wise what to do.

1048
00:45:49,204 --> 00:45:51,289
Yeah, can't I just hear
Lefty's wife

1049
00:45:51,331 --> 00:45:54,209
yelping with joy at the sight
of me.

1050
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:56,294
You haven't any cause
to worry about Maggie.

1051
00:45:56,336 --> 00:45:58,380
You two would get along swell.

1052
00:45:58,421 --> 00:46:00,882
Baby boy, I know females,

1053
00:46:00,924 --> 00:46:02,467
you don't.

1054
00:46:02,509 --> 00:46:04,177
I got an idea what's
on your mind

1055
00:46:04,219 --> 00:46:06,113
but Maggie ain't the kind
of a dame you're meaning.

1056
00:46:06,137 --> 00:46:08,139
She's square from the toes up.

1057
00:46:08,181 --> 00:46:10,016
Funny thing, them that kick
highest

1058
00:46:10,058 --> 00:46:11,768
always seem to settle down
hardest.

1059
00:46:15,480 --> 00:46:17,190
You mean this Maggie was sort
of gay

1060
00:46:17,232 --> 00:46:18,650
before Lefty came along?

1061
00:46:18,692 --> 00:46:20,568
Lefty met her in Honolulu.

1062
00:46:20,610 --> 00:46:21,879
They were both nuts over
each other

1063
00:46:21,903 --> 00:46:23,238
right from the start.

1064
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:24,072
It never mattered
to either of them

1065
00:46:24,114 --> 00:46:25,490
that they met in Evolay.

1066
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:29,452
In Evolay?

1067
00:46:29,494 --> 00:46:30,412
Yeah.

1068
00:46:30,453 --> 00:46:31,555
Knowing the worst to begin with

1069
00:46:31,579 --> 00:46:33,373
isn't always the worst way
to begin.

1070
00:46:34,708 --> 00:46:36,418
Of course,
if there's some reason

1071
00:46:36,459 --> 00:46:38,545
why you're set for a Apia,

1072
00:46:38,586 --> 00:46:41,840
if there's someone you're
wanting to see there,

1073
00:46:41,881 --> 00:46:44,342
I wouldn't want to persuade you.

1074
00:46:44,384 --> 00:46:46,469
I'm not
looking forward to a Apia

1075
00:46:46,511 --> 00:46:48,013
with any wild joy.

1076
00:46:48,054 --> 00:46:49,306
Then there's another thing.

1077
00:46:49,347 --> 00:46:51,182
If you go to Sydney now,

1078
00:46:51,224 --> 00:46:53,685
I'll be hovering in sight
in a few weeks.

1079
00:46:53,727 --> 00:46:56,146
Not that that might mean
so much to you maybe.

1080
00:46:58,189 --> 00:46:59,816
I haven't so many friends,
handsome,

1081
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:01,693
but what I could do
with one more.

1082
00:47:06,531 --> 00:47:09,701
You know, you're an awful
funny fella, handsome.

1083
00:47:09,743 --> 00:47:11,870
I guess I'm the
dumbbell king, all right.

1084
00:47:17,459 --> 00:47:19,127
Have they any kids?

1085
00:47:19,169 --> 00:47:20,503
Who?

1086
00:47:20,545 --> 00:47:22,672
Those friends of yours in
Sydney.

1087
00:47:22,714 --> 00:47:25,300
Oh, I was thinking
of something else.

1088
00:47:25,342 --> 00:47:26,426
Yep, two.

1089
00:47:27,510 --> 00:47:28,510
How about it?

1090
00:47:29,888 --> 00:47:31,306
Huh? How about what?

1091
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:34,059
Changing your route and
going to Sydney instead.

1092
00:47:34,100 --> 00:47:35,602
Sure, why not?

1093
00:47:35,643 --> 00:47:38,396
I guess no one can stop
me from doing that.

1094
00:47:38,438 --> 00:47:39,230
What a simp I was,

1095
00:47:39,272 --> 00:47:42,108
getting my wind up all over
nothing.

1096
00:47:42,150 --> 00:47:43,610
Here I was jumping with the
shakes

1097
00:47:43,651 --> 00:47:44,527
and nervous as a witch

1098
00:47:44,569 --> 00:47:47,197
'cause that dismal crumb
wouldn't let me go to Apia.

1099
00:47:47,238 --> 00:47:48,698
Well, Apia my foot.

1100
00:47:48,740 --> 00:47:50,116
It's Sydney for mine.

1101
00:47:54,621 --> 00:47:56,456
It's for you.

1102
00:47:56,498 --> 00:47:57,290
For me?

1103
00:47:57,332 --> 00:48:01,836
Who's writing me a letter?

1104
00:48:02,879 --> 00:48:05,215
It's from the governor's office.

1105
00:48:05,256 --> 00:48:07,258
You better open it.

1106
00:48:21,064 --> 00:48:23,149
What's the matter?

1107
00:48:23,191 --> 00:48:24,317
I won't go back.

1108
00:48:24,359 --> 00:48:26,194
They can't make me, there's
reasons.

1109
00:48:26,236 --> 00:48:27,445
I got some rights, haven't I?

1110
00:48:27,487 --> 00:48:28,655
What's the matter?

1111
00:48:28,696 --> 00:48:30,824
The governor's ordered
me back to San Francisco.

1112
00:48:30,865 --> 00:48:32,075
Now, don't get nervous.

1113
00:48:32,117 --> 00:48:33,451
I'll tell you what you do.

1114
00:48:33,493 --> 00:48:34,411
You go and see the governor.

1115
00:48:34,452 --> 00:48:35,679
Ask him as a favor
to let you stay here

1116
00:48:35,703 --> 00:48:36,806
until the Sydney boat leaves.

1117
00:48:36,830 --> 00:48:38,182
That'll only be three
or four more days.

1118
00:48:38,206 --> 00:48:39,040
Will he see me?

1119
00:48:39,082 --> 00:48:39,874
Hurry up before he goes
to supper.

1120
00:48:39,916 --> 00:48:40,708
It's only a few steps.

1121
00:48:40,750 --> 00:48:41,584
Do you want me to go with you?

1122
00:48:41,626 --> 00:48:42,419
Yeah, will you?

1123
00:48:42,460 --> 00:48:44,546
Wait'll I'll get my coat
and I'll make him listen.

1124
00:48:58,309 --> 00:48:59,310
So, you're back, are ya?

1125
00:48:59,352 --> 00:49:01,438
You low-down skunk.

1126
00:49:01,479 --> 00:49:03,290
What have you been telling
the governor about me?

1127
00:49:03,314 --> 00:49:04,750
I've been hoping to have
another talk

1128
00:49:04,774 --> 00:49:05,567
with you, Miss Thompson.

1129
00:49:05,608 --> 00:49:07,777
Why, you miserable
snail-snatcher.

1130
00:49:07,819 --> 00:49:08,879
I wouldn't talk to you
if you and me

1131
00:49:08,903 --> 00:49:10,905
were the only two people
left on Earth.

1132
00:49:10,947 --> 00:49:12,824
Why, you're so doggone
mean it makes me sick

1133
00:49:12,866 --> 00:49:13,950
even to look at you.

1134
00:49:13,992 --> 00:49:15,285
That's what I think of you.

1135
00:49:15,326 --> 00:49:16,578
Coming to me with all that guff

1136
00:49:16,619 --> 00:49:18,121
you spilled about salvation,

1137
00:49:18,163 --> 00:49:20,081
then going and having me
deported on top of it.

1138
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:21,308
- Why, you low lizard.
- Sadie.

1139
00:49:21,332 --> 00:49:22,292
I'm wholly indifferent to the
abuse

1140
00:49:22,333 --> 00:49:23,918
you think fit to heap upon me.

1141
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:26,504
Filling the governor with
a lot of filthy lies about me

1142
00:49:26,546 --> 00:49:29,466
and now this comes so I got
to beat it on the next boat.

1143
00:49:29,507 --> 00:49:30,901
I hardly expect him
to let you stay

1144
00:49:30,925 --> 00:49:31,843
under the circumstances.

1145
00:49:31,885 --> 00:49:33,070
Yeah, well, what did the
governor know

1146
00:49:33,094 --> 00:49:34,280
or care about me until you went
and hauled

1147
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:35,430
your hooks into me?

1148
00:49:35,472 --> 00:49:36,973
It's you that did it,
you did it all!

1149
00:49:37,015 --> 00:49:38,617
I don't want to deceive
you, Miss Thompson.

1150
00:49:38,641 --> 00:49:39,743
I urged the governor to take

1151
00:49:39,767 --> 00:49:41,978
the only steps consistent
with his obligation.

1152
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:43,396
Well, why couldn't you
let me be?

1153
00:49:43,438 --> 00:49:44,481
Was I doing you any harm?

1154
00:49:44,522 --> 00:49:45,875
You may rest assured
if you had been,

1155
00:49:45,899 --> 00:49:47,484
I'd be the last one
to resent it.

1156
00:49:47,525 --> 00:49:49,170
You don't think I want to
stay in this rain hole, do you?

1157
00:49:49,194 --> 00:49:51,738
You're being given every
opportunity of getting out.

1158
00:49:51,779 --> 00:49:53,048
Come on Sadie, don't say
anymore.

1159
00:49:53,072 --> 00:49:54,949
You, I know your kind.

1160
00:49:54,991 --> 00:49:56,701
You dirty two-faced mutt.

1161
00:49:56,743 --> 00:49:57,619
I bet when you were a kid,

1162
00:49:57,660 --> 00:49:59,787
you caught flies and tore
their wings off.

1163
00:49:59,829 --> 00:50:01,831
I bet you stuck pins in
frogs just to see them

1164
00:50:01,873 --> 00:50:03,642
wiggle and flap while
you run them electrical.

1165
00:50:03,666 --> 00:50:04,834
I know you.

1166
00:50:04,876 --> 00:50:06,604
Why, you'd tear the heart
out of your grandmother

1167
00:50:06,628 --> 00:50:07,587
if she didn't think your way

1168
00:50:07,629 --> 00:50:09,297
and tell her you were saving
her soul,

1169
00:50:09,339 --> 00:50:10,840
you Psalm-singing son of a...

1170
00:50:13,384 --> 00:50:14,260
You will be glad to hear

1171
00:50:14,302 --> 00:50:16,262
that the governor
has acted at last.

1172
00:50:16,304 --> 00:50:17,722
He's a weak man.

1173
00:50:17,764 --> 00:50:19,057
For days, he has shilly-shallied

1174
00:50:19,098 --> 00:50:21,142
saying it was none of his
concern.

1175
00:50:21,184 --> 00:50:23,144
I can readily see why.

1176
00:50:23,186 --> 00:50:24,437
How did you convince him?

1177
00:50:25,688 --> 00:50:28,191
I finally had to speak
straight to his shoulder.

1178
00:50:29,234 --> 00:50:30,994
The foundation that I
represent in Washington

1179
00:50:31,027 --> 00:50:33,196
is not entirely without
influence.

1180
00:50:33,238 --> 00:50:35,740
Miss Thompson will sail on
the next boat that goes.

1181
00:50:35,782 --> 00:50:36,950
How soon will that be?

1182
00:50:36,991 --> 00:50:40,203
The Golden Gate is due here
from Sydney next Tuesday.

1183
00:50:40,245 --> 00:50:41,329
She will sail on that.

1184
00:50:42,372 --> 00:50:43,706
Four days more.

1185
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:46,500
Are you ready?

1186
00:50:52,590 --> 00:50:56,094
Well, that settles Sadie
Thompson's hash, I guess.

1187
00:51:04,978 --> 00:51:07,564
Mrs. Davidson told me that
she hasn't closed her eyes

1188
00:51:07,605 --> 00:51:08,982
ever since that girl came

1189
00:51:09,023 --> 00:51:10,567
to live under the same roof
as her.

1190
00:51:10,608 --> 00:51:13,945
The founder of her
religion wasn't so squeamish.

1191
00:51:13,987 --> 00:51:16,155
Don't joke about such
things, please, Robert.

1192
00:51:16,197 --> 00:51:19,284
Excuse me Doc, Miss
Thompson isn't feeling well.

1193
00:51:19,325 --> 00:51:20,577
Will you see her for a moment?

1194
00:51:20,618 --> 00:51:21,619
Certainly.

1195
00:51:24,539 --> 00:51:25,665
She's right out here.

1196
00:51:35,425 --> 00:51:37,427
Sorry you're not feeling well.

1197
00:51:37,468 --> 00:51:40,054
I'm well enough,
not really sick.

1198
00:51:40,096 --> 00:51:42,223
O'Hara said that just
"cause I had to see you.

1199
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:43,391
Yes, Miss Thompson.

1200
00:51:43,433 --> 00:51:45,768
I gotta get back
for inspection now.

1201
00:51:45,810 --> 00:51:47,228
I'll see you later.

1202
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:48,313
Keep your chin up.

1203
00:51:48,354 --> 00:51:49,354
Thanks, handsome.

1204
00:51:53,901 --> 00:51:55,403
Lucky meeting, Sarge.

1205
00:51:55,445 --> 00:51:56,237
What's up?

1206
00:51:56,279 --> 00:51:58,448
Hey, what have you been
doing lately?

1207
00:51:58,489 --> 00:51:59,741
You're booked for the brig.

1208
00:51:59,782 --> 00:52:01,034
That's right, Sarge.

1209
00:52:01,075 --> 00:52:02,285
Fall in.

1210
00:52:02,327 --> 00:52:03,327
Okay.

1211
00:52:04,370 --> 00:52:06,998
I don't know exactly
what I can do.

1212
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,100
I thought maybe you
wouldn't mind

1213
00:52:08,124 --> 00:52:10,585
asking him if he'd let me
wait and go to Sydney instead.

1214
00:52:10,627 --> 00:52:12,712
It's only three or four days
longer.

1215
00:52:12,754 --> 00:52:13,546
I'll ask him.

1216
00:52:13,588 --> 00:52:15,840
Tell him I can get work
in Sydney, straight stuff.

1217
00:52:15,882 --> 00:52:17,776
Tell him I just can't go
back to San Francisco now,

1218
00:52:17,800 --> 00:52:19,010
there's reasons.

1219
00:52:19,052 --> 00:52:20,052
Will you, please?

1220
00:52:21,012 --> 00:52:22,221
I'll do what I can.

1221
00:52:22,263 --> 00:52:23,973
Thank you, thank you.

1222
00:52:25,975 --> 00:52:27,935
- Oh, Davidson?
- What is it, Doctor?

1223
00:52:27,977 --> 00:52:29,687
I want to speak to you
about something,

1224
00:52:29,729 --> 00:52:30,813
shall I come up?

1225
00:52:30,855 --> 00:52:34,567
- No, I'll come right down.
- Tell him I ask his pardon.

1226
00:52:34,609 --> 00:52:35,401
Tell him I'm sorry.

1227
00:52:35,443 --> 00:52:37,445
Better get into your
room now, Miss Thompson.

1228
00:52:42,742 --> 00:52:44,452
Well Doctor, what can I do
for you?

1229
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:47,538
It's about Miss Thompson.

1230
00:52:47,580 --> 00:52:49,957
The governor has told her
that if you have no objection,

1231
00:52:49,999 --> 00:52:51,268
he will allow her to remain here

1232
00:52:51,292 --> 00:52:52,877
until she can take the boat for
Sydney.

1233
00:52:52,919 --> 00:52:53,961
I'm sorry, Doctor,

1234
00:52:54,003 --> 00:52:55,838
but it is useless to discuss
the matter.

1235
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:57,800
It appears the girl has
reasons for not wanting

1236
00:52:57,840 --> 00:52:59,592
to return to San Francisco.

1237
00:52:59,634 --> 00:53:01,219
I don't see that it makes any
difference

1238
00:53:01,260 --> 00:53:02,970
if she goes to Sydney instead.

1239
00:53:03,012 --> 00:53:04,156
It's only a matter
of a few days.

1240
00:53:04,180 --> 00:53:06,265
Well, you mean this
interference for the best

1241
00:53:06,307 --> 00:53:08,309
but my mind is made up.

1242
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:09,578
You want to know what I think?

1243
00:53:09,602 --> 00:53:11,646
I think you're harsh and
tyrannical.

1244
00:53:11,688 --> 00:53:14,649
I'm terribly sorry you should
think that of me, Doctor.

1245
00:53:14,691 --> 00:53:15,942
Believe me, my heart bleeds

1246
00:53:15,983 --> 00:53:18,194
for that unfortunate young woman

1247
00:53:18,236 --> 00:53:21,614
I cannot find in my conscience
to change my decision.

1248
00:53:21,656 --> 00:53:23,216
However, if the governor wishes
to do so

1249
00:53:23,241 --> 00:53:25,201
on his own account, that is his
business.

1250
00:53:25,243 --> 00:53:26,243
He won't,

1251
00:53:27,328 --> 00:53:29,038
and you know why.

1252
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:30,474
Please don't bare any malice
toward me

1253
00:53:30,498 --> 00:53:32,959
because I cannot exceed
to your wish.

1254
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:35,378
I respect you very much, Dr.
MacPhail

1255
00:53:35,420 --> 00:53:36,522
and I should be sorry indeed

1256
00:53:36,546 --> 00:53:37,463
if you thought ill of me.

1257
00:53:37,505 --> 00:53:39,340
I have no doubt you have a
sufficiently

1258
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:42,510
good opinion of yourself to
bear mine with equanimity.

1259
00:53:57,567 --> 00:53:58,567
I'm sorry.

1260
00:54:02,905 --> 00:54:04,449
Don't give up hope, Miss
Thompson.

1261
00:54:04,490 --> 00:54:06,576
I think it's a shame the
way they're treating you.

1262
00:54:06,617 --> 00:54:08,494
I'll go and see the governor
myself.

1263
00:54:09,746 --> 00:54:10,746
Will you?

1264
00:54:12,373 --> 00:54:13,166
Will you now?

1265
00:54:13,207 --> 00:54:15,042
- Now.
- Oh, you're awful good,

1266
00:54:15,084 --> 00:54:16,084
awful good.

1267
00:54:17,420 --> 00:54:19,338
You don't know what this
means to me, Doctor.

1268
00:54:19,380 --> 00:54:20,173
Don't cry, Miss Thompson.

1269
00:54:20,214 --> 00:54:21,299
I think I can do something.

1270
00:54:21,340 --> 00:54:22,550
God bless you.

1271
00:54:37,732 --> 00:54:40,234
Dear to the lord.

1272
00:54:55,082 --> 00:54:56,876
Me tell you something.

1273
00:54:57,877 --> 00:55:01,005
Mr. Davidson.

1274
00:55:01,047 --> 00:55:02,548
What's that?

1275
00:55:02,590 --> 00:55:04,175
What are you saying?

1276
00:55:04,217 --> 00:55:09,222
All the same I know.

1277
00:55:18,481 --> 00:55:19,774
What's she saying?

1278
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:22,401
What were you saying, Ameena?

1279
00:55:22,443 --> 00:55:26,405
All the same I know.

1280
00:55:26,447 --> 00:55:27,240
A witch doctor.

1281
00:55:27,281 --> 00:55:30,243
A species of wizards of the sea.

1282
00:55:30,284 --> 00:55:32,954
Knew everything, saw everything.

1283
00:55:32,995 --> 00:55:34,497
Lived by the power of God.

1284
00:55:35,540 --> 00:55:38,876
A real goat charmer had no
charms for him.

1285
00:55:38,918 --> 00:55:41,295
When hungry, he simply
ferreted out a devil

1286
00:55:41,337 --> 00:55:42,213
and ate him up for tea.

1287
00:55:42,255 --> 00:55:44,090
Ah, cut it.

1288
00:55:44,131 --> 00:55:46,300
That kind of talk gives me
the willies.

1289
00:55:50,763 --> 00:55:52,473
Let me have a drink,
will ya, Joe?

1290
00:55:56,936 --> 00:55:58,896
That's Davidson up there,
isn't it?

1291
00:55:58,938 --> 00:56:00,314
Sounds like his voice.

1292
00:56:00,356 --> 00:56:01,482
What's he saying?

1293
00:56:02,316 --> 00:56:04,151
He's saying, "Amen."

1294
00:56:11,784 --> 00:56:15,121
Either that stuff's jinxed
or I am, Horn.

1295
00:56:15,162 --> 00:56:17,164
I can't seem to feel it.

1296
00:56:18,249 --> 00:56:19,625
Maybe the Atua is after me.

1297
00:56:22,295 --> 00:56:23,754
