Now why would you do that?

1550
01:08:18,594 --> 01:08:20,762
I'd do that so as I wouldn't
be blamed for anything

1551
01:08:20,804 --> 01:08:22,639
in case anything happened.

1552
01:08:22,681 --> 01:08:24,516
Sounds like another row is
starting.

1553
01:08:25,392 --> 01:08:27,185
The most unlucky day of my life

1554
01:08:27,227 --> 01:08:29,730
is the day that
came into port.

1555
01:08:29,771 --> 01:08:31,231
Ameena,

1556
01:08:31,273 --> 01:08:32,273
lock up.

1557
01:08:33,066 --> 01:08:34,443
I like my comfort.

1558
01:08:35,319 --> 01:08:38,196
For five days now, this
whole household has centered

1559
01:08:38,238 --> 01:08:40,240
on that tormented Thompson girl
in there

1560
01:08:41,074 --> 01:08:44,453
with Davidson and Old Nick
wrestling for her soul.

1561
01:08:44,494 --> 01:08:45,954
It's got me nervous.

1562
01:08:45,996 --> 01:08:48,665
Cheer up, it won't center
around her much longer.

1563
01:08:48,707 --> 01:08:49,958
What do you know about it?

1564
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:51,460
Safe in the brig all week.

1565
01:08:52,544 --> 01:08:54,504
There hasn't been such
a casting out of devils

1566
01:08:54,546 --> 01:08:56,256
since the first chapter of
Exodus.

1567
01:08:57,215 --> 01:08:59,051
The last vestige of mortal sin

1568
01:08:59,092 --> 01:09:00,719
lurking in that poor critter's
heart

1569
01:09:00,761 --> 01:09:01,762
has been torn out.

1570
01:09:02,679 --> 01:09:05,807
The Sadie Thompson who blew
into my hotel a week ago

1571
01:09:05,849 --> 01:09:06,849
isn't anymore.

1572
01:09:07,643 --> 01:09:08,977
Wait 'til you see her.

1573
01:09:09,019 --> 01:09:10,859
Aren't keeping anything
from me, are you Joe?

1574
01:09:10,896 --> 01:09:12,939
Wait 'til you see her, I say.

1575
01:09:12,981 --> 01:09:14,858
She's like a victim
they've got trussed up

1576
01:09:14,900 --> 01:09:16,818
to sacrifice to some
bloody idol.

1577
01:09:17,694 --> 01:09:20,364
Yeah, it'll make you sick to
look at her.

1578
01:09:20,405 --> 01:09:21,198
Get her out for me,

1579
01:09:21,239 --> 01:09:22,342
I'll tend to the rest of this.

1580
01:09:22,366 --> 01:09:23,575
Gladly.

1581
01:09:23,617 --> 01:09:26,620
My mind is blank save
for one fact.

1582
01:09:26,662 --> 01:09:29,456
Tomorrow Miss Sadie Thompson
will be on the high seas.

1583
01:09:29,498 --> 01:09:30,832
You bet she'll be.

1584
01:09:32,626 --> 01:09:34,044
Miss Thompson, you're wanted.

1585
01:09:34,086 --> 01:09:35,754
All right.

1586
01:09:49,393 --> 01:09:52,312
Sadie, you look awful sick.

1587
01:09:54,356 --> 01:09:56,942
I was wondering whether
I'd see you before I left.

1588
01:09:57,859 --> 01:09:59,111
You've been awful kind.

1589
01:10:00,404 --> 01:10:01,488
I'll never forget it.

1590
01:10:02,823 --> 01:10:04,199
I want to thank you.

1591
01:10:09,871 --> 01:10:11,415
Look here, Sadie,

1592
01:10:11,456 --> 01:10:13,750
how long will it take you
to get packed?

1593
01:10:13,792 --> 01:10:15,293
I'm pretty well packed now.

1594
01:10:15,335 --> 01:10:16,461
That's good,

1595
01:10:16,503 --> 01:10:18,839
Briggs and Hudson will
be along any minute.

1596
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,424
They're to tote your bags.

1597
01:10:20,465 --> 01:10:23,510
You hurry up now and get
dressed as fast as you can.

1598
01:10:23,552 --> 01:10:25,137
Get dressed?

1599
01:10:25,178 --> 01:10:26,888
You're leaving this place
tonight.

1600
01:10:29,182 --> 01:10:32,060
My boat don't leave
until tomorrow morning.

1601
01:10:32,102 --> 01:10:33,478
Your boat's leaving tonight

1602
01:10:33,520 --> 01:10:35,731
and I'm going to see you
get aboard it.

1603
01:10:35,772 --> 01:10:37,566
I must wait for Mr. Davidson.

1604
01:10:37,607 --> 01:10:39,693
He's going to see me on board.

1605
01:10:40,694 --> 01:10:44,281
Mr. Davidson isn't going to
see you off.

1606
01:10:44,322 --> 01:10:45,949
He isn't?

1607
01:10:45,991 --> 01:10:48,285
What's happened? Where is he?

1608
01:10:49,119 --> 01:10:49,911
You're not going to San
Francisco,

1609
01:10:49,953 --> 01:10:51,830
that's what's happened.

1610
01:10:51,872 --> 01:10:52,831
You're leaving here in a few
minutes

1611
01:10:52,873 --> 01:10:54,541
for the Samarcan Islands
and a junk.

1612
01:10:54,583 --> 01:10:56,060
You're to wait there until
the Sydney boat comes along

1613
01:10:56,084 --> 01:10:57,419
and then you're going
to Sydney.

1614
01:11:01,173 --> 01:11:04,551
But, what do you suppose
Mr. Davidson would say

1615
01:11:04,593 --> 01:11:07,429
if he came back
and found me gone?

1616
01:11:07,471 --> 01:11:09,848
You know the old
shout-out better than I do

1617
01:11:09,890 --> 01:11:10,807
but I don't mind admitting

1618
01:11:10,849 --> 01:11:11,909
that the sight of his face
at that moment

1619
01:11:11,933 --> 01:11:13,810
would slip me considerable,
quiet fun.

1620
01:11:24,362 --> 01:11:27,115
You've had a pretty bad time
these last few days, I guess.

1621
01:11:27,157 --> 01:11:28,492
Just forget him.

1622
01:11:28,533 --> 01:11:30,410
That's mighty sweet
and fine of you

1623
01:11:30,452 --> 01:11:32,204
to go through all this trouble
for me.

1624
01:11:32,245 --> 01:11:34,372
Fine, fine nothing.

1625
01:11:34,414 --> 01:11:35,624
This ain't one small bit

1626
01:11:35,665 --> 01:11:38,043
of what I'd like to do for
you, if I got the chance.

1627
01:11:38,084 --> 01:11:40,587
You know, your doing this

1628
01:11:41,755 --> 01:11:45,050
sort of makes me want
to cry but-

1629
01:11:45,091 --> 01:11:46,718
- But what?

1630
01:11:46,760 --> 01:11:48,762
I can't do it.

1631
01:11:48,804 --> 01:11:49,930
Why can't you do it?

1632
01:11:51,765 --> 01:11:54,893
I'm going through with what
I've got to go through with.

1633
01:11:54,935 --> 01:11:56,353
Are you afraid of Davidson?

1634
01:11:57,229 --> 01:11:58,188
He'll never get a hold of you
again,

1635
01:11:58,230 --> 01:11:59,523
I'll see to that.

1636
01:11:59,564 --> 01:12:02,275
No, that isn't it.

1637
01:12:02,317 --> 01:12:04,861
It'd be awful hard for
me to make you understand

1638
01:12:04,903 --> 01:12:05,946
what's come over me.

1639
01:12:07,030 --> 01:12:08,740
I can't understand it myself

1640
01:12:08,782 --> 01:12:11,159
except that it's happened.

1641
01:12:11,201 --> 01:12:14,162
Sadie, this sort of
thing don't make you happy.

1642
01:12:14,204 --> 01:12:15,872
You don't realize it ain't
yourself.

1643
01:12:15,914 --> 01:12:18,333
You've got to forget Mr.
Davidson,

1644
01:12:18,375 --> 01:12:20,335
and come with me.

1645
01:12:21,586 --> 01:12:23,505
No, I couldn't.

1646
01:12:23,547 --> 01:12:24,881
I couldn't.

1647
01:12:24,923 --> 01:12:26,925
You don't know
what you're saying.

1648
01:12:26,967 --> 01:12:29,094
You haven't any idea
what you're saying.

1649
01:12:29,135 --> 01:12:30,446
They're not gonna send you
back there

1650
01:12:30,470 --> 01:12:32,430
with no one to take care of you.

1651
01:12:32,472 --> 01:12:33,741
In Sydney, in a couple of weeks,

1652
01:12:33,765 --> 01:12:35,100
you'll have me.

1653
01:12:36,560 --> 01:12:38,895
Remember what I told you
about Lefty and Maggie?

1654
01:12:38,937 --> 01:12:39,813
I won't listen,

1655
01:12:39,855 --> 01:12:41,439
I won't listen.

1656
01:12:41,481 --> 01:12:42,625
What's to hinder you repenting
in Sydney

1657
01:12:42,649 --> 01:12:44,860
as well as in San Francisco,

1658
01:12:44,901 --> 01:12:46,278
if you got to repent?

1659
01:12:46,319 --> 01:12:48,280
Oh, you don't understand.

1660
01:12:50,073 --> 01:12:53,451
I've got to go back and be
punished for what I've been.

1661
01:12:54,995 --> 01:12:56,413
What's that you're saying?

1662
01:12:59,249 --> 01:13:01,710
When I get back to
San Francisco, handsome,

1663
01:13:03,003 --> 01:13:05,589
I've got to go to the
penitentiary for three years.

1664
01:13:10,302 --> 01:13:11,302
Gee.

1665
01:13:12,679 --> 01:13:16,850
Mr. Davidson says it
doesn't make any difference

1666
01:13:16,892 --> 01:13:18,768
whether I was innocent or guilty

1667
01:13:19,853 --> 01:13:21,187
of what they framed me for.

1668
01:13:22,814 --> 01:13:23,899
He says

1669
01:13:25,275 --> 01:13:28,361
it's the only way of
letting me square myself.

1670
01:13:30,238 --> 01:13:35,118
He says I've got to accept
an unjust punishment

1671
01:13:35,160 --> 01:13:38,538
by man as a sacrifice
for my sins.

1672
01:13:40,290 --> 01:13:41,809
Oh, you listen to me,
get in your room

1673
01:13:41,833 --> 01:13:43,311
and throw your clothes
on as fast as you can.

1674
01:13:43,335 --> 01:13:44,502
Let go of me.

1675
01:13:44,544 --> 01:13:45,962
Let go.

1676
01:13:46,004 --> 01:13:47,881
Don't you dare do that again.

1677
01:13:47,923 --> 01:13:49,382
I want you to go away,
do you hear?

1678
01:13:49,424 --> 01:13:50,216
Go away.

1679
01:13:50,258 --> 01:13:52,427
- Sadie, Sadie.
- I mean it, go away.

1680
01:13:52,469 --> 01:13:54,429
Aw, Sadie, listen please.

1681
01:13:54,471 --> 01:13:56,264
Aw, handsome, why
can't you let me alone?

1682
01:13:56,306 --> 01:13:58,433
Here are the boys, Sadie.

1683
01:13:58,475 --> 01:14:00,352
Come to say goodbye to you.

1684
01:14:00,393 --> 01:14:02,413
They're going to put your
things aboard the junk for you.

1685
01:14:02,437 --> 01:14:03,438
No, don't.

1686
01:14:04,522 --> 01:14:07,484
Why doesn't Mr. Davidson come?

1687
01:14:07,525 --> 01:14:08,860
Where is he?

1688
01:14:08,902 --> 01:14:09,903
Where is he?

1689
01:14:12,113 --> 01:14:13,591
See if there isn't a coat
or something in that room,

1690
01:14:13,615 --> 01:14:15,301
that old peeler's got
her like she's tranced.

1691
01:14:15,325 --> 01:14:17,369
We're taking her whether
she wants to go or not.

1692
01:14:22,457 --> 01:14:24,709
They're taking my things.

1693
01:14:24,751 --> 01:14:25,919
They mustn't take my things.

1694
01:14:25,961 --> 01:14:27,438
- Sadie, don't.
- Someone will hear you.

1695
01:14:27,462 --> 01:14:29,756
Let me go, go away.

1696
01:14:29,798 --> 01:14:32,968
Oh, handsome,
why can't you let me be?

1697
01:14:37,514 --> 01:14:38,890
Don't you see, Sadie,

1698
01:14:38,932 --> 01:14:40,308
you ain't yourself?

1699
01:14:40,350 --> 01:14:42,352
I am, I am myself.

1700
01:14:43,770 --> 01:14:45,814
That's what I've been
trying to tell you.

1701
01:14:47,273 --> 01:14:49,109
Mr. Davidson's a holy man.

1702
01:14:49,985 --> 01:14:51,653
He's different from you and me.

1703
01:14:52,570 --> 01:14:54,447
He's made me different.

1704
01:14:54,489 --> 01:14:56,866
I've been born all over again,
handsome.

1705
01:14:56,908 --> 01:14:58,451
Can't you see?

1706
01:14:58,493 --> 01:14:59,285
Yes, I see

1707
01:14:59,327 --> 01:15:01,413
and I see something else.

1708
01:15:01,454 --> 01:15:03,307
Remember I told you if
you ever needed a friend,

1709
01:15:03,331 --> 01:15:04,791
I'd be here?

1710
01:15:04,833 --> 01:15:06,793
Well, you need a friend right
now.

1711
01:15:06,835 --> 01:15:09,170
You're not going to San
Francisco.

1712
01:15:09,212 --> 01:15:10,964
You're going to Sydney.

1713
01:15:11,006 --> 01:15:14,968
Sadie, out there you've got
your whole life before you.

1714
01:15:15,010 --> 01:15:16,219
We go away where this rain

1715
01:15:16,261 --> 01:15:18,221
or anything else
can't bother us,

1716
01:15:18,263 --> 01:15:20,015
just you and me,

1717
01:15:20,056 --> 01:15:22,225
like Lefty and Maggie.

1718
01:15:22,267 --> 01:15:23,309
Fifty-fifty.

1719
01:15:24,394 --> 01:15:26,104
You'll be Mrs. Tim O'Hara.

1720
01:15:27,063 --> 01:15:28,148
It's Sydney and us,

1721
01:15:28,189 --> 01:15:31,526
the whole works against the
penitentiary

1722
01:15:31,568 --> 01:15:33,570
and I'm taking you whether
you want to go or not.

1723
01:15:33,611 --> 01:15:35,238
No, no you mustn't.

1724
01:15:35,280 --> 01:15:36,280
You mustn't.

1725
01:15:38,783 --> 01:15:40,035
I'm saved, I tell you.

1726
01:15:40,076 --> 01:15:41,536
You'll send me to hell.

1727
01:15:41,578 --> 01:15:44,164
Mr. Davidson, Mr. Da...

1728
01:15:44,998 --> 01:15:46,916
Seems I got here just about
in time.

1729
01:15:48,126 --> 01:15:49,562
All evening, I had
a peculiar feeling

1730
01:15:49,586 --> 01:15:50,628
you were in danger.

1731
01:15:50,670 --> 01:15:53,173
Sadie, don't pay any attention
to him.

1732
01:15:53,214 --> 01:15:54,549
I'm sorry for you, O'Hara,

1733
01:15:54,591 --> 01:15:56,843
what you are trying to
do is a serious offense.

1734
01:15:56,885 --> 01:15:58,928
What you're trying to
do would make a hyena cry.

1735
01:15:58,970 --> 01:16:00,430
By trying to abduct Sadie
Thompson,

1736
01:16:00,472 --> 01:16:01,949
you've made an attempt
to defeat the law

1737
01:16:01,973 --> 01:16:03,200
and it's likely to go hard
with you.

1738
01:16:03,224 --> 01:16:04,392
That's my lookout.

1739
01:16:04,434 --> 01:16:05,661
What kind of a man are you,
anyway?

1740
01:16:05,685 --> 01:16:07,187
Picking on this poor kid here,

1741
01:16:07,228 --> 01:16:08,730
getting her so she's half-crazy.

1742
01:16:08,772 --> 01:16:10,583
Sending her so she'd have
to go back to prison.

1743
01:16:10,607 --> 01:16:12,275
You're one choice specimen,
Davidson,

1744
01:16:12,317 --> 01:16:13,568
I'll say that for you.

1745
01:16:13,610 --> 01:16:15,111
They don't make your kind
everyday.

1746
01:16:15,153 --> 01:16:16,905
You are a reckless,
headstrong man O'Hara.

1747
01:16:16,946 --> 01:16:17,864
You are breaking barracks

1748
01:16:17,906 --> 01:16:19,324
and attempting a high-handed
crime.

1749
01:16:19,365 --> 01:16:21,326
You defy the authority
of State and God.

1750
01:16:21,367 --> 01:16:22,720
You cannot go on the way
you are going

1751
01:16:22,744 --> 01:16:24,329
and I shall see to it that you
do not.

1752
01:16:24,370 --> 01:16:25,789
Begging your pardon,
might I ask,

1753
01:16:25,830 --> 01:16:26,748
what you think you're gonna
do about it?

1754
01:16:26,790 --> 01:16:27,933
Get back to your
barracks as fast as you can

1755
01:16:27,957 --> 01:16:30,752
and report here to me tomorrow
after Miss Thompson is gone.

1756
01:16:30,794 --> 01:16:33,254
Ha, where do you get these
ideas anyway?

1757
01:16:33,296 --> 01:16:35,465
If it's good advice you
want to ladle out, keep it.

1758
01:16:35,507 --> 01:16:36,883
On such rare moments as I think,

1759
01:16:36,925 --> 01:16:38,218
I think for myself.

1760
01:16:38,259 --> 01:16:39,445
This is not helping your case.

1761
01:16:39,469 --> 01:16:40,261
Watch what you say.

1762
01:16:40,303 --> 01:16:41,387
I'm here to watch out

1763
01:16:41,429 --> 01:16:42,972
that Sadie don't make any fool
breaks.

1764
01:16:43,014 --> 01:16:44,033
You've got to do some settling
with me

1765
01:16:44,057 --> 01:16:45,350
before she does any sailing.

1766
01:16:45,391 --> 01:16:46,935
You're wrong.

1767
01:16:46,976 --> 01:16:48,353
I know what I'm doing.

1768
01:16:48,394 --> 01:16:50,188
I'm sorry but I see clear.

1769
01:16:51,272 --> 01:16:52,440
See clear?

1770
01:16:52,482 --> 01:16:54,359
Why he's got you so
it's like you're doped.

1771
01:16:54,400 --> 01:16:55,860
I see what you don't see.

1772
01:16:57,070 --> 01:17:00,156
What's happened to me
don't happen to everybody.

1773
01:17:00,198 --> 01:17:01,616
I was nothing.

1774
01:17:01,658 --> 01:17:02,658
I was nobody.

1775
01:17:03,535 --> 01:17:05,161
Now I'm something.

1776
01:17:05,203 --> 01:17:06,203
I'm somebody.

1777
01:17:07,247 --> 01:17:08,832
It's a wonderful thing to know

1778
01:17:08,873 --> 01:17:11,376
you're being made of some
account.

1779
01:17:11,417 --> 01:17:14,712
The only thing I can't see
is how it's happened to me.

1780
01:17:17,132 --> 01:17:18,925
Is that the way it is, Sadie?

1781
01:17:20,051 --> 01:17:21,051
Yes.

1782
01:17:22,178 --> 01:17:24,514
What do you want me to do?

1783
01:17:25,974 --> 01:17:28,977
I don't want you to do
anything

1784
01:17:29,018 --> 01:17:32,021
except just don't say
anything more.

1785
01:17:34,399 --> 01:17:38,403
All right, I'll tell the
boys to bring your things back.

1786
01:17:40,947 --> 01:17:45,869
Sadie, if you and me never
see each other again,

1787
01:17:47,996 --> 01:17:48,997
I want to say this.

1788
01:17:51,040 --> 01:17:52,167
I'll never forget you,

1789
01:17:54,043 --> 01:17:55,043
ever.

1790
01:18:03,678 --> 01:18:04,929
If you'd like,

1791
01:18:06,222 --> 01:18:07,223
I'll come back tomorrow

1792
01:18:07,265 --> 01:18:09,434
and put your things
aboard the boat for you,

1793
01:18:10,977 --> 01:18:12,103
if you want me to.

1794
01:18:26,201 --> 01:18:28,411
- Don't blame O'Hara, Mr.
- Davidson.

1795
01:18:29,412 --> 01:18:31,831
It was all my fault.

1796
01:18:31,873 --> 01:18:32,665
No, my poor child,

1797
01:18:32,707 --> 01:18:34,209
it was not your fault.

1798
01:18:35,293 --> 01:18:36,252
In the last few days,

1799
01:18:36,294 --> 01:18:39,631
you've become very close and
dear to God.

1800
01:18:39,672 --> 01:18:41,883
He has tested you and found you
true.

1801
01:18:41,925 --> 01:18:43,927
Tonight, he sent the devil
to tempt you

1802
01:18:43,968 --> 01:18:45,511
but you thrust away the devil.

1803
01:18:46,930 --> 01:18:49,098
Once your soul lay
like a stagnant pool

1804
01:18:49,140 --> 01:18:51,726
in the lowest pit of the
deepest valley,

1805
01:18:51,768 --> 01:18:53,937
but tonight it has lifted
to the sun,

1806
01:18:55,396 --> 01:18:58,358
cleansed, glorified as the rain
of heaven.

1807
01:19:00,693 --> 01:19:03,571
When you're here, everything's
clear.

1808
01:19:04,822 --> 01:19:05,949
Everything's all right.

1809
01:19:06,908 --> 01:19:08,660
But when you're away,

1810
01:19:09,702 --> 01:19:10,702
I'm afraid.

1811
01:19:12,497 --> 01:19:14,916
I get to thinking how wicked
I used to be

1812
01:19:16,000 --> 01:19:19,212
and I just can't believe
it's all forgiven.

1813
01:19:21,381 --> 01:19:22,507
The days aren't so bad

1814
01:19:22,548 --> 01:19:24,342
but it's the nights.

1815
01:19:26,094 --> 01:19:27,720
Then I begin to think and wonder

1816
01:19:28,805 --> 01:19:29,805
if they're bad now,

1817
01:19:31,766 --> 01:19:33,601
what are they gonna be like

1818
01:19:33,643 --> 01:19:35,561
when you can't come to me
anymore,

1819
01:19:35,603 --> 01:19:36,688
when I'm alone?

1820
01:19:36,729 --> 01:19:37,522
When you're alone,

1821
01:19:37,563 --> 01:19:39,649
my strength will come
to you through prayers

1822
01:19:39,691 --> 01:19:42,402
which will always be on my lips.

1823
01:19:42,443 --> 01:19:43,236
Little by little,

1824
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:45,863
you yourself will grow stronger,
surer,

1825
01:19:45,905 --> 01:19:47,407
and presently the time will come

1826
01:19:47,448 --> 01:19:49,617
when sin and terror will be
powerless

1827
01:19:49,659 --> 01:19:52,954
to penetrate the great love
that God has wrapped around you.

1828
01:19:53,955 --> 01:19:56,416
Then will you be redeemed,

1829
01:19:56,457 --> 01:19:58,459
the Kingdom and the Glory
will be yours.

1830
01:20:00,044 --> 01:20:01,462
Yes.

1831
01:20:01,504 --> 01:20:02,504
Yes.

1832
01:20:03,548 --> 01:20:05,758
When you talk like that,

1833
01:20:05,800 --> 01:20:06,843
I'm not afraid.

1834
01:20:08,428 --> 01:20:12,140
That old life I led don't
belong to me at all.

1835
01:20:13,433 --> 01:20:14,433
It wasn't me,

1836
01:20:15,393 --> 01:20:16,394
it was someone else.

1837
01:20:17,812 --> 01:20:20,565
When I feel like that, Mr.
Davidson,

1838
01:20:21,399 --> 01:20:24,068
does it mean I'm redeemed?

1839
01:20:24,110 --> 01:20:25,737
Yes, Sadie.

1840
01:20:25,778 --> 01:20:27,613
Tomorrow will be a very busy day
for you.

1841
01:20:27,655 --> 01:20:29,157
You'll need all your strength.

1842
01:20:30,241 --> 01:20:32,035
You must try and
get some sleep now.

1843
01:20:38,041 --> 01:20:39,459
No.

1844
01:20:39,500 --> 01:20:40,500
But,

1845
01:20:41,419 --> 01:20:44,797
if I wake up tonight
and get afraid,

1846
01:20:44,839 --> 01:20:46,007
can I call you?

1847
01:20:46,049 --> 01:20:47,091
When I hear you call,

1848
01:20:47,133 --> 01:20:48,133
I will come.

1849
01:20:50,720 --> 01:20:52,305
I'm really tired.

1850
01:21:19,874 --> 01:21:22,251
Hello, Horn, you still up?

1851
01:21:22,293 --> 01:21:23,920
Yep, reading.

1852
01:21:23,961 --> 01:21:24,754
Want anything?

1853
01:21:24,796 --> 01:21:26,381
Nope, I'm off to bed.

1854
01:21:27,840 --> 01:21:30,927
There's an uncanny concentration
about the rain tonight.

1855
01:21:32,136 --> 01:21:33,179
Perhaps.

1856
01:21:33,221 --> 01:21:34,514
Everybody in?

1857
01:21:34,555 --> 01:21:37,392
Davidson is still out,
can't sleep.

1858
01:21:37,433 --> 01:21:38,935
Can't sleep, eh?

1859
01:21:38,976 --> 01:21:42,271
Has uneasy dreams,
his wife tells me.

1860
01:21:45,650 --> 01:21:46,943
'Night.

1861
01:21:46,984 --> 01:21:47,985
Goodnight.

1862
01:22:04,293 --> 01:22:07,588
Everything goeth,
everything returneth,

1863
01:22:07,630 --> 01:22:09,757
so rolleth the wheel of
existence.

1864
01:22:10,883 --> 01:22:14,095
Everything dieth, everything
marches forth again.

1865
01:22:15,096 --> 01:22:17,140
So runneth the year of
existence.

1866
01:22:24,105 --> 01:22:25,273
Thus spake Zarathustra.

1867
01:22:47,712 --> 01:22:48,712
Mr. Davidson.

1868
01:22:50,173 --> 01:22:52,508
Hello Miss Thompson,
what are you up for?

1869
01:22:52,550 --> 01:22:54,760
I couldn't sleep.

1870
01:22:54,802 --> 01:22:56,471
It's this rain and those drums,

1871
01:22:57,972 --> 01:23:00,600
and then thinking about
tomorrow.

1872
01:23:03,269 --> 01:23:06,022
I don't seem to be able to
do much by myself, do I?

1873
01:23:06,063 --> 01:23:06,898
Not yet maybe,

1874
01:23:06,939 --> 01:23:09,400
but every prayer is going
to make you stronger.

1875
01:23:12,028 --> 01:23:13,196
This time tomorrow,

1876
01:23:13,237 --> 01:23:14,322
I'll be on the sea.

1877
01:23:17,074 --> 01:23:19,160
I don't suppose we'll
ever meet again.

1878
01:23:19,202 --> 01:23:22,205
Not in this life, Sadie,
probably.

1879
01:23:23,164 --> 01:23:25,249
I'll be in prison three years.

1880
01:23:26,334 --> 01:23:27,543
That's a long time.

1881
01:23:29,212 --> 01:23:31,464
What'll I do when I come out?

1882
01:23:31,506 --> 01:23:32,506
What'll I be?

1883
01:23:33,716 --> 01:23:37,428
For hours and hours, I've been
wondering.

1884
01:23:37,470 --> 01:23:40,097
Out there in the rain,
I walked and wondered too.

1885
01:23:40,139 --> 01:23:42,517
The darkness was full of eyes.

1886
01:23:42,558 --> 01:23:45,394
I saw things I never saw before.

1887
01:23:45,436 --> 01:23:48,189
I looked into the awful
groves of Astroth herself.

1888
01:23:50,733 --> 01:23:53,528
Sadie, you don't have to
go back to San Francisco.

1889
01:23:54,862 --> 01:23:56,531
- What do you mean?
- Just that.

1890
01:23:58,824 --> 01:24:01,035
Didn't you tell me I
had to make a sacrifice?

1891
01:24:01,077 --> 01:24:03,287
Yes, but I repeat you
don't have to go back

1892
01:24:03,329 --> 01:24:04,622
unless you truly want to.

1893
01:24:05,456 --> 01:24:07,583
But I do want to.

1894
01:24:07,625 --> 01:24:09,794
I haven't got anything else
to offer.

1895
01:24:09,835 --> 01:24:12,004
It's the only thing
I've got to give

1896
01:24:12,046 --> 01:24:13,422
and I want to give it.

1897
01:24:13,464 --> 01:24:14,882
I thank thee.

1898
01:24:14,924 --> 01:24:15,925
I thank thee.

1899
01:24:17,301 --> 01:24:19,554
- Why do you say that, Mr.
- Davidson?

1900
01:24:19,595 --> 01:24:21,889
Because you said what
I knew you'd say.

1901
01:24:21,931 --> 01:24:24,850
My every prayer
has been answered.

1902
01:24:24,892 --> 01:24:26,852
I prayed that there might
come into your heart.

1903
01:24:26,894 --> 01:24:29,438
So passionate a desire
for this punishment

1904
01:24:29,480 --> 01:24:31,107
which you now lay
as a thank offering

1905
01:24:31,148 --> 01:24:34,569
at your redeemer's feet that
even if I offered to let you go

1906
01:24:34,610 --> 01:24:35,987
you would refuse.

1907
01:24:36,028 --> 01:24:39,865
I hope I'll be strong enough
to go through with it right.

1908
01:24:41,200 --> 01:24:42,511
From now on,
you will be strong.

1909
01:24:42,535 --> 01:24:44,579
There is to be no more fear.

1910
01:24:46,497 --> 01:24:48,666
Radiant, beautiful,

1911
01:24:50,543 --> 01:24:52,670
you'll be one of the
daughters of the King.

1912
01:24:54,630 --> 01:24:56,132
That's what you are now, Sadie,

1913
01:24:56,173 --> 01:24:57,842
one of the daughters
of the King,

1914
01:24:59,093 --> 01:25:00,761
radiant, beautiful.

1915
01:25:04,390 --> 01:25:06,934
I think I'll go now

1916
01:25:06,976 --> 01:25:09,145
and try to get some sleep.

1917
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:18,918
It's Davidson.

1918
01:28:18,959 --> 01:28:19,919
He isn't dead, is he?

1919
01:28:19,960 --> 01:28:20,753
Throat's cut.

1920
01:28:20,795 --> 01:28:21,962
Been dead for several hours.

1921
01:28:22,004 --> 01:28:22,797
Suicide.

1922
01:28:22,838 --> 01:28:23,798
I must tell Mrs. Davidson.

1923
01:28:23,839 --> 01:28:25,758
No, I'll go back and tell her.

1924
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:28,219
I hate to do it but I guess
she knows something already.

1925
01:28:28,260 --> 01:28:29,804
She heard the boys
calling for you.

1926
01:28:29,845 --> 01:28:30,845
Better hurry.

1927
01:28:35,893 --> 01:28:37,478
I wonder why he did it.

1928
01:29:04,463 --> 01:29:05,463
Joe.

1929
01:29:06,715 --> 01:29:08,050
Where's Miss Thompson?

1930
01:29:08,092 --> 01:29:08,884
How did you know about it?

1931
01:29:08,926 --> 01:29:09,802
One of the boys told me.

1932
01:29:09,844 --> 01:29:10,904
I came over here
as fast as I could

1933
01:29:10,928 --> 01:29:12,263
in case Sadie needed me.

1934
01:29:12,304 --> 01:29:13,430
You don't think,

1935
01:29:13,472 --> 01:29:14,223
there isn't any chance

1936
01:29:14,265 --> 01:29:15,534
of Sadie being mixed up in this,
is there?

1937
01:29:15,558 --> 01:29:17,601
No, he did it himself.

1938
01:29:17,643 --> 01:29:19,520
I hope they don't bring him
in here.

1939
01:29:19,562 --> 01:29:21,313
I don't like men that die
that way.

1940
01:29:21,355 --> 01:29:22,231
They don't rest easy.

1941
01:29:22,273 --> 01:29:23,273
Wait a minute.

1942
01:29:33,117 --> 01:29:34,159
Pretty cool, I'll say.

1943
01:29:34,201 --> 01:29:37,329
Yeah, well, anyway I'm glad
I didn't have to tell her.

1944
01:29:37,371 --> 01:29:38,956
I wonder how she'll take it.

1945
01:29:40,082 --> 01:29:41,142
I wonder,

1946
01:29:41,166 --> 01:29:42,626
Now what?

1947
01:29:42,668 --> 01:29:43,668
Listen to that.

1948
01:29:47,172 --> 01:29:49,008
See? She don't know yet.

1949
01:29:49,049 --> 01:29:50,801
Man, why is she playing?

1950
01:29:52,177 --> 01:29:53,405
One of us ought to go in
and tell her what's happened.

1951
01:29:53,429 --> 01:29:55,139
She hasn't touched that thing

1952
01:29:55,180 --> 01:29:56,807
since Davidson went after her.

1953
01:29:56,849 --> 01:29:58,934
What's she playing it now for?

1954
01:29:58,976 --> 01:29:59,768
I don't know.

1955
01:29:59,810 --> 01:30:01,645
Look here, last night
she was frightened

1956
01:30:01,687 --> 01:30:04,148
and all-in about going
back to San Francisco.

1957
01:30:04,189 --> 01:30:06,901
Why is she playing that thing
the first thing this morning

1958
01:30:06,942 --> 01:30:10,029
when at noon she's going on a
journey she's afraid to make?

1959
01:30:10,070 --> 01:30:10,946
Why?

1960
01:30:10,988 --> 01:30:12,197
How should I know?

1961
01:30:12,239 --> 01:30:14,366
- What do you infer?
- I'm not inferring.

1962
01:30:14,408 --> 01:30:15,993
Who's gonna tell her, you?

1963
01:30:17,202 --> 01:30:18,746
It'll come better from you.

1964
01:30:18,787 --> 01:30:19,997
Oh, all right.

1965
01:30:24,501 --> 01:30:25,294
Miss Thompson?

1966
01:30:25,336 --> 01:30:26,587
Yeah, what is it?

1967
01:30:26,629 --> 01:30:27,963
Let me in, it's Horn.

1968
01:30:28,005 --> 01:30:29,048
Oh no, you don't.

1969
01:30:29,089 --> 01:30:29,965
Stay where you are.

1970
01:30:30,007 --> 01:30:31,050
Be out in a minute.

1971
01:30:31,091 --> 01:30:32,593
It's very important, Miss
Thompson.

1972
01:30:32,635 --> 01:30:34,637
Okay, coming right up.

1973
01:30:47,107 --> 01:30:49,151
Hello, Horn, what's going on?

1974
01:30:51,028 --> 01:30:53,906
Hello, handsome, what are
you doing up so early?

1975
01:30:53,948 --> 01:30:54,948
Sadie.

1976
01:30:57,868 --> 01:31:00,579
Surprised to see me all dolled
up, huh?

1977
01:31:00,621 --> 01:31:01,621
Well, why not?

1978
01:31:02,581 --> 01:31:03,374
I had to put on my best

1979
01:31:03,415 --> 01:31:06,919
this gay and glorious morning,
didn't I?

1980
01:31:06,961 --> 01:31:09,088
Besides I'm radiant, beautiful.

1981
01:31:10,547 --> 01:31:12,049
You didn't know that, did you?

1982
01:31:13,592 --> 01:31:14,385
I could hardly believe my eyes

1983
01:31:14,426 --> 01:31:16,762
when I saw that sun
this morning.

1984
01:31:16,804 --> 01:31:18,347
Do I feel fine?

1985
01:31:18,389 --> 01:31:19,431
I do.

1986
01:31:20,516 --> 01:31:21,308
I'd race you down to the beach

1987
01:31:21,350 --> 01:31:23,102
if it wasn't for these
pesky heels.

1988
01:31:23,143 --> 01:31:25,145
Sadie, turn off that
phonograph.

1989
01:31:25,187 --> 01:31:27,064
- Why?
- They'll be back any minute.

1990
01:31:27,106 --> 01:31:29,024
- Who?
- Mrs. Davidson.

1991
01:31:30,651 --> 01:31:32,653
And why should I turn off the
phonograph

1992
01:31:32,695 --> 01:31:34,655
because Mrs. Davidson's coming
back?

1993
01:31:35,656 --> 01:31:38,409
I'm not concerned with
what Mrs. Davidson thinks

1994
01:31:38,450 --> 01:31:41,662
or for that matter, with
what Mr. Davidson thinks.

1995
01:31:41,704 --> 01:31:43,580
My advice to him is
to pin on his wings

1996
01:31:43,622 --> 01:31:44,873
and try the air.

1997
01:31:44,915 --> 01:31:46,059
Joe, turn off that phonograph.

1998
01:31:46,083 --> 01:31:47,710
Stay out of my room, Joe.

1999
01:31:47,751 --> 01:31:49,128
That phonograph stays on.

2000
01:31:49,169 --> 01:31:50,438
Sadie, something has happened.

2001
01:31:50,462 --> 01:31:53,257
You bet something's happened.

2002
01:31:53,298 --> 01:31:54,550
You men.

2003
01:31:54,591 --> 01:31:55,591
Pigs.

2004
01:31:59,013 --> 01:32:01,682
Sadie,
Davidson's killed himself.

2005
01:32:01,724 --> 01:32:03,308
What?

2006
01:32:03,350 --> 01:32:05,060
They found him on the beach
this morning

2007
01:32:05,102 --> 01:32:06,103
with his throat cut.

2008
01:32:10,816 --> 01:32:12,234
Killed himself.

2009
01:32:14,528 --> 01:32:16,238
Then I can forgive him.

2010
01:32:17,573 --> 01:32:19,283
I thought the joke was all on me

2011
01:32:21,368 --> 01:32:22,911
but I see it wasn't.

2012
01:32:24,288 --> 01:32:25,873
Joe.

2013
01:32:25,914 --> 01:32:26,914
Please.

2014
01:32:41,013 --> 01:32:43,682
No offense to you in that
last crack I made, handsome.

2015
01:32:44,892 --> 01:32:46,643
Oh, that's all right.

2016
01:32:48,103 --> 01:32:49,772
I'm going to Sydney with you

2017
01:32:49,813 --> 01:32:51,857
if the invitation
still holds good.

2018
01:33:14,213 --> 01:33:15,213
Let's go.

2019
01:33:23,514 --> 01:33:25,140
I understand, Miss Thompson.

2020
01:33:27,476 --> 01:33:29,061
I'm sorry for him

2021
01:33:30,104 --> 01:33:31,730
and I'm sorry for you.

2022
01:33:34,483 --> 01:33:38,403
I'm sorry for everybody
in the world, I guess.

